title: light corn bread(for sausage, pear, corn bread stuffing)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly coat an 8-inch baking pan with nonstick spray. In bowl, put milk, corn meal, oil and egg white; whisk to combine. In larger bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, pepper and baking soda. Stir milk mixture into the larger bowl just until batter is moistened. Pour the batter into pan. Smooth top evenly with spatula. Bake until top is golden and springs back to touch, about 25 minutes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Dice potatoes.
In 2-quart pan add potatoes and onions to boiling water.
Cook until tender, mash slightly.
Do not drain. Add enough milk to make 5 cups.
Blend melted butter.
Add flour, parsley, salt and pepper; cook.
Add cheese until melted.
Serve.

title: swedish cabbage rolls
directions: In a bowl, combine egg, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, onion and milk; mix well.
Add ground beef and cooked rice; beat together with fork.
Immerse cabbage leaves in boiling water for 3 minutes or until limp; drain.
Place 1/2 cup meat mixture on each leaf; fold sides and roll ends over meat.
Place rolls in 12 x 7 1/2 x 1-inch baking dish.
Blend together soup, brown sugar and lemon juice; pour over cabbage rolls.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Baste once or twice with sauce.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions.
Mix broccoli in casserole dish with mayonnaise, soup and cheese.
Brown bread crumbs in butter.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake until bubbling, about 45 minutes to an hour at 375°.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add oats, syrup and vanilla.
Pat into 7 x 11-inch greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt chips and peanut butter. Cool and spread over cooked batter and sprinkle with nuts.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour into a baked nine-inch pie shell.
Beat the egg whites.
Fold into 1/3 cup sugar.
Brown in moderate oven.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on the package and drain.
Stir cheeses, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper together in a mixing bowl. In a wide, shallow baking dish, spread some spaghetti sauce evenly just to cover the bottom.
Gently stuff the cooked shells with cheese mixture and arrange in baking dish.
Pour the remaining spaghetti sauce over the shells and top with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with a tossed salad and warm bread.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: punch
directions: Use strawberry, lemon or lime flavors. Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: risotto
directions: *Or 1 pound tender green asparagus, cut into 1-inch pieces or a handful of dried porcini, soaked in water.

title: slow cooker sloppy joes
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, brown ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper; drain.
Place ground beef mixture in slow cooker. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low setting for 3 to 5 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve on sandwich buns. Makes 21 (1/3-cup) servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers and garlic in pan.
Mix salt in.
Mix in 2 trays of ice.
Put one tray of ice on top.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain ice water and remove garlic cloves.

title: shortcake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix into that the flour, salt and baking powder.
Heat the milk and margarine separate, then add to other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in an oblong pan at 350° until done.
Serve with strawberries and milk.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in milk. In a bowl, combine sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Blend with mixer. Add flour and buttermilk, then knead the dough, adding 2 additional cups of flour. Refrigerate 1 hour. Roll out and cut with cookie cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle sugar on top of cookie. (May decorate with raisins, if desired.) Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: potato cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Cream together until fluffy, sugar and shortening.
Beat in thoroughly 4 eggs.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Fold in mashed potatoes.
Add coffee and milk mixture alternately with flour; fold in raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 275° oven 45 minutes or until done. Cool and ice with chocolate frosting.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place zucchini in a baking dish and pour sauce over it.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Return to oven and bake another 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: crispy cinnamon baked chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a blender.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken in buttermilk, then crumbs.
Place in greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet; bake and cool.
Mix together the cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dill weed; spread over cooled crust.
Chop the vegetables up finely; sprinkle on top. Sprinkle on cheese and bacon.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mushroom soup(zupa grzybowa)
directions: Cook the carrots, parsley, celery and 1 onion in 4 cups salted water for 20 minutes; strain. Cook the mushrooms and the second onion in 1 cup water for 10 minutes. Add salt and pepper. Cover with the vegetable broth. Add the flour mixed with 1/4 cup cold water. Boil. Remove from heat. Add sour cream, dill and parsley. Add noodles or fine macaroni. Serves 8.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a huge bowl, let your two year old combine all the ingredients.
Have your child mash, knead and squeeze, it says, "until you feel better" and until there aren't any lumps of butter.
Your child may need some help, but he can form the dough into small balls himself, not as big as a walnut, and put them on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Butter the bottom of a glass and have your child dip it in granulated sugar.
This is what he uses to flatten each ball of dough, dipping it into the sugar each time.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Remove when lightly browned.
Cool a few minutes and crisp on a rack. Store in a tight container.
The dough keeps well in the refrigerator.
Yields 15 dozen.

title: punch
directions: Serve in punch bowl over a block of ice.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Brown ground beef in a medium skillet.
Drain.
Add mint and garlic; cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Spoon ground beef mixture into a large bowl.
Stir in pasta, tomatoes, cheese, red bell pepper and onion.
Add dressing and lemon juice; toss lightly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve on lettuce-covered salad plates.
Serves 4.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Put peanut butter on soda crackers.
Place marshmallows on top.
Place under broiler and watch closely until marshmallows are brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Cook rice until tender. Saute onions in butter.
Mix with broccoli and rice.
Dilute soup with milk; add can of mushrooms and pour over mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Spread out the bean dip.
Crush avocados and add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Layer all the ingredients in the order given (very important, ending with cheese) on one large platter or 2 small platters.
Good with tortilla chips or any of your favorite dip chips or crackers.
Good for large parties or can be broken down to half recipe.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients; pour into graham cracker crusts and chill 1 hour.

title: out of this world bars
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix condensed milk and coconut.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: asparagus casserole #1
directions: Drain asparagus; remove 1/2 cup liquid.
Make white sauce of butter, flour, milk and asparagus liquid.
Add salt and pepper, then stir in cheese until melted.
Place asparagus in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, then layer with eggs.
Pour sauce over eggs and top with almonds.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut each potato in 8 wedges.
Put wedges on shallow pan.
Brush combined ingredients over wedges. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Do not turn.
Baste 2 to 3 times during baking.

title: carrot bars
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 1/2 to 2 cans of rolls. Cream together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread mixture over rolls in pan.
Cover with other 1 1/2 to 2 cans of rolls.

title: chicken cheese bake
directions: Place chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top each piece with slice of cheese.
Lay sliced mushrooms on top of cheese. Mix soup with wine and pour on top. Spread on stuffing mix and drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 egg and oil; stir until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup and press remaining mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
In another bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and remaining egg until fluffy.
Spread over cake.
Sprinkle with remaining cake mixture. Bake for another 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breast in covered dish overnight in sauce. Next evening bake in a 350° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes.
This can be barbecued on a grill.

title: braided easter bread
directions: Heat butter and milk to 120° to 130°.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar, salt, yeast and 1 1/2 cups flour in a large bowl.
Add milk mixture, combining thoroughly.
Add cardamon, cinnamon, lemon peel, aniseed and egg; mix thoroughly.
Add remaining flour in small amounts until a soft dough.
Knead until smooth (approximately 10 minutes).
Place in greased bowl, coating all sides; cover with damp towel.
Set in warm place to double (about an hour).

title: chinese-style vegetables
directions: In medium skillet, mix water and vegetables.
Cover.
Steam 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring several times.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in soy sauce.
Makes 4 servings (40 calories each).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain and put in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese over broccoli.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add well beaten eggs.
Heat vinegar with butter and celery seed to boiling point.
Pour slowly into egg mixture while stirring.
Return to stove.
Cook until thick.

title: emily's delight
directions: In a large bowl, fold together first 3 ingredients.
Next drain fruits and add; mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add meat and brown, salt and pepper, tomato sauce and garlic.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: two hour buns
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Knead.
Let raise 1 hour.
Put in small pans.
Let raise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Thoroughly wash beans. Add water. Soak overnight (or simmer 2 minutes, then soak 1 hour).
Don't drain. Add ham bone, salt, peppers and bay leaf. Cover and simmer about 3 to 3 1/2 hours, adding sliced onion the last 1/2 hour.
Remove ham bone.
Mash beans slightly using potato masher.
Cut ham off bone. Return to soup. Season to taste.
Makes 6 servings.

title: three cheese ball
directions: Leave cheeses out for 2 hours at room temperature.
Whip all ingredients together, except nuts, in mixing bowl until mixed thoroughly.
Spread nuts on waxed paper.
Form ingredients into ball and roll in nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: cookie pops
directions: You will need popsicle sticks.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat salad oil.
Add chicken and brown lightly.
Sprinkle salt over chicken.
Combine salsa, spaghetti sauce mix and Snap-E Tom. Mix well.
(Can add small amount of water, if needed.)
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Serve with spaghetti.
Very good Mexican-Italian taste.

title: wake-up casserole
directions: Makes 4 servings.
Prep: 20 minutes.
Chill: 30 minutes. Broil: 12 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O, sugar, boiling water and cold water.
Put into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Set aside.
Mix together in blender the cranberries, pecans or walnuts, apple, sweet orange, pineapple and lemon juice.
Add to Jell-O and chill.

title: jan's turtle cheesecake
directions: Melt the caramels with enough milk to make a creamy consistency.
Pour over crust.
Toast the pecans by placing in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add the pecans on top of the caramels.
Beat the cream cheese with the sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the sour cream and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool. Melt the chocolate chips with the whipping cream and top cake.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Cook onion and ginger root in butter until onion is soft.
Add squash, broth, water and garlic and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes until squash is tender.
Puree mixture.
Stir in lime juice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve warm.

title: cucumber salad dressing
directions: Measure first 4 ingredients into small bowl.
Peel 1/2 cucumber.
Remove seeds.
Chop finely or process in food processor.
Add to mixture.
Mix with spoon.
Place covered into the refrigerator and chill 1/2 hour.

title: dad's caramel corn
directions: Combine popcorn and nuts in a large container and keep warm in a 250° oven.
In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook to 290° on candy thermometer (hard-crack stage).
Slowly pour over popcorn and nuts, stirring to coat.
Spread mixture in buttered 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Return to 250° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir after 10 minutes.
Cool and break in pieces.

title: chilled vegetable salad
directions: Put green beans, peas and corn in a bowl with cover.
Add pimento, celery, green pepper and onions.
Boil sugar, vinegar, oil, water, salt and pepper; then chill.
After dressing is chilled, pour over vegetables and chill together at least 4 hours.

title: basic meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy with the cream of tartar added. Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine water, sugar and yeast. Add salt and 2 cups flour. Mix with mixer for 2 minutes. Add eggs and shortening. Blend in rest of flour. Stir until well formed. Rest 20 minutes.

title: black-eyed salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: zanny dip
directions: Run onion and jalapenos through fine food grinder or blender. Melt cheese in double boiler and allow to cool.
Mix all with electric mixer, then place in jars.
Keeps in refrigerator indefinitely.
Makes approximately 2 quarts of dip.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: granny grace's whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add whipping cream, vanilla and lemon; beat.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage stew
directions: In a large saucepan add all ingredients, except potatoes (or macaroni or rice).
Simmer 1 hour, covered.
Add potato (or macaroni or rice).
Cook until done, adding water as necessary for stew.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: mud puddle cake
directions: Place dry ingredients directly into a 9-inch square pan.
Mix well. Make 3 indentations in this mixture.
Place oil in first, vinegar in second and vanilla in third. Drizzle water over all and mix well.

title: shrimp vera cruz(microwave recipe)
directions: Combine onion, pepper, oil and garlic in shallow baking dish. Cook on High 3 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, wine, oregano, salt, cumin and pepper sauce.
Cover with waxed paper and cook on High 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and toss lightly to coat with sauce. Cook on High until shrimp just turns pink, 5 to 7 minutes. Garnish with parsley.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together and put into loaf pan.
Do not add salt. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients except last two.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with corn flakes and butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick chocolate candy
directions: Melt the chocolate pieces in a saucepan over water.
Stir in the peanuts.
Turn into small pan.
Chill before breaking into pieces.

title: cheesecake dreams
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
In small bowl mix first 3 ingredients, stir in melted butter.
Reserve 1/3 cup crumbs.
Pat remaining gently into pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in small bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes until set.
Cool on wire rack, then cut into 2-inch squares, cut again in half.
About 85 calories each.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Make angel cake or purchase.
Slice into 3 layers.
Layer with mixture of frosting, partially congealed jello and frozen strawberries.
Frost cooled cake.

title: cheesy chili success
directions: Prepare Success rice according to directions.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat until cheese is melted. Stir to blend well.
Serve over hot rice.
Garnish with pepper or tomato if desired.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix all together and form into small balls.
Roll in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 7 or 8 minutes.
Don't overbake or let them get brown.
They will be soft.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion;
add salt and pepper.
Add remaining
ingredients
except
for beans, cheese
and
chips. Cook for 30 minutes over medium heat.
Add	beans.	Pour
into casserole and top with cheese and chips
(crushed).
Bake
for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into quarters.
Cook, using package directions.
Drain.
Combine all of the ingredients together. Marinate in refrigerator for six hours or overnight.
Serve at room temperature.
Yields 12 servings.

title: *golden dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Place sugar and salt in large mixing bowl; set aside.
Heat and stir milk and shortening until shortening melts.
Add to mixing bowl along with eggs and yeast mixture.
Stir in 1 cup of flour at a time to form a soft dough that can be kneaded.
Knead on lightly floured board until smooth and elastic.
Place in large, greased bowl.
Cover.

title: sky high coconut cream pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of the sugar, cornstarch and salt into a heavy medium size saucepan.
Stir in milk; cook over low heat, stirring gently but constantly, until mixture thickens and boils for 3 minutes.
Beat egg yolks well in a small bowl.
Slowly stir in 1/2 cup of the hot mixture, then stir back into saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter or margarine, vanilla and 1/4 cup of the coconut.
Pour into pastry shell.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams and reserve juice.
Combine all ingredients, adding clam juice back into mixture to make dipping consistency.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients real good and refrigerate overnight.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pie filling and undrained crushed pineapple.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, coconut and nuts and spread over pie filling and pineapple.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix cooked meat, onions, carrots, Vietnamese noodles, monosodium glutamate, pepper, salt, sugar and cabbage.
Put into spring roll shell and roll up.
Coat with eggs.
Fry in skillet. Deep fry.

title: easy double decker fudge(microwave)
directions: In a glass measure cup, combine peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Cook on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Stir until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract.
Spread evenly into a foil-lined 8-inch square pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add raisins, apples and nuts.
Mix flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to apple mixture and mix by hand.
Add vanilla.
Bake one hour at 350° in Bundt pan.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and press into 13 x 9 pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Note:
If nuts are omitted, add an additional 1/2 cup chocolate semi-sweet chips (optional).

title: creamy autumn potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a 1-quart casserole dish.
In 1-quart saucepan, saute in butter over medium heat, the frozen Ore-Ida chopped onions and garlic until tender.
Stir in undiluted soup and cream cheese cubes; cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and hot.
In casserole, alternately layer frozen potatoes and hot cream cheese sauce, ending with a sauce layer.
Cover and bake 45 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and potatoes are tender. Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Yield:
4 to 5 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Squeeze lemon juice on fish.
Mix with remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake in greased loaf pan for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Loaf will begin to brown on top when done.

title: berry mallow yam bake
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and cinnamon.
Cut in the margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Toss 1 cup crumb mixture with the sweet potatoes in a 1-quart casserole.
Put cranberries on top, then remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken slowly in hot shortening.
Add 1 cup water, bouillon and salt; mix well.
Cover and simmer until tender. Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook in saucepan over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat and add sauce to chicken.
Stir in pineapple chunks, green pepper and onion; cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over hot white rice.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper; dredge meat.
Brown slowly.
Add remaining ingredients except onions.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add onions, cover and bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: broccoli lasagna
directions: In undiluted soup, heat frozen or fresh broccoli. In 1 tablespoon oil, cook onion until light brown. Add carrots. Reduce heat to low. Add 1/4 cup of water; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until tender. Remove to bowl.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss to mix well.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough on cookie sheet like pizza.
Mix egg yolks, seasonings and oil together.
Spread on dough.
Cover with pepperoni, ham and cheese.
Roll like jelly roll.
Place seam down and brush dough with egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Slice and serve with pizza sauce, if desired.

title: coconut pecan brownies
directions: In large mixing bowl, add all the above ingredients, mixing well. Bake at 350° for 42 to 52 minutes in a 9 by 13 inch pan.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, whip cream cheese until smooth.
Add drained pineapple, 1 cup chopped pecans, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining cup of pecans.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate until well chilled or overnight.
Garnish with pineapple slice and cherry. Serve with crackers.

title: biscuit pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large skillet brown beef.
Drain and stir in soup, corn, tomatoes, green onions and basil.
Bring to boil.
Pour into ungreased 10 x 6-inch (1 1/2-quart) baking dish. Separate biscuits.
Arrange in 2 rows.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 14 to 16 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 4.

title: smoked pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put potatoes and onion in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Cover with chops.
Blend soup and milk; pour over chops.
Add peas.
Cover tightly.
Bake
1 3/4 to 2 hours.

title: hamburger casserole pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Place in bottom of casserole dish. Add Lipton onion soup (dry).
Sprinkle over meat.
Pour sweet peas on top of meat.
Add mashed potatoes; cover completely.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until cheese is melted and is bubbly.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and cook celery and onions until tender.
Use shortening, if necessary. Stir to separate meat. Pour off fat. Stir in soup, salt and thyme.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole pan.
Spoon potatoes around edge of casserole pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Bake and cool one pie shell.
Wash and hull strawberries. Cut up one cup of strawberries.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
In saucepan, slowly add 1 cup water to sugar mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Add the cup of chopped berries.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and clear.
Add a few drops of red food coloring and cool.
Stir in remaining berries, saving 1/4 cup for garnish.
Pour into pie shell and cool for about 3 hours. Garnish with remaining berries and serve.
May also top with whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: shrewsburg squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Take 1/2 and spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put layer of jam on top. Then add remainder of mixture.
Sprinkle with white sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven until delicate brown.
Cut in squares.

title: ricotta stuffed chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Beat breasts to 6-inch rectangles.
Place 1/4 cup Ricotta mixture on short end of each breast.
Fold in the long sides and roll, starting at the edge with the cheese.
Place in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, seam side down.
Microwave 8 to 11 minutes.
Heat sauce; pour over chicken. Sprinkle with Mozzarella.

title: pineapple pecan cake frosting
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Slowly add powdered sugar until mixed well.
Use with Pineapple Pecan Cake.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix shortening, egg, sugar and molasses.
Beat well.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add gradually to other mixture.
Add 1/2 cup of boiling water.
To other 1/2 cup of water, add 1 teaspoon soda. Add last.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Will be a little tacky on top.
Good served plain or with Cool Whip.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cool for 1 hour.
Grate cheese.
Add red beans, cubed tomatoes, onion and avocados (all should be cubed). Right before serving, mix all ingredients together (chips last).

title: pepper steak
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice diagonally across grain into 3 x 1/2-inch strips and set aside.
Heat oil in a large skillet; add steak and cook, stirring often, until steak is browned.
Combine 1 cup water, soy sauce, molasses, ginger and garlic; mix well and pour over steak.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add onion; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add green peppers and water chestnuts; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine 1/4 cup water and cornstarch; mix well and add to skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Stir in tomatoes.

title: baked spinach
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sugar coated peanuts(kids recipe)
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in saucepan over medium heat.
Add peanuts and continue to cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Cook until peanuts are completely sugared (coated and no syrup).

title: corn chowder
directions: In a casserole dish place a layer of sliced potatoes, a layer of onion, a layer of corn and a thin layer of cracker crumbs. Repeat until ingredients are gone.
Cover top with a layer of cracker crumbs; add milk over all.
Place butter pieces over top. Bake at 350° from 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until potatoes are tender.

title: mexican frito pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain off fat.
Add chili and tomato sauce.
Let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Spoon sauce in bottom of casserole, just enough to cover.
Crush Fritos and place a layer on top of sauce.
Now put a thicker layer of sauce, then sour cream, then Cheddar cheese.
Start again with another layer ending with Fritos.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Garnish with bell pepper slices. Bake 2 hours in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: easy french bread
directions: Place 1/2 cubed bread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cream cheese.
Top with rest of cubed bread.
Pour eggs, milk and syrup over mixture.
Cover with plastic and refrigerate. Leave overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12. Lovely for a brunch.

title: caramel cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and beat until smooth. Beat in eggs until smooth. Stir in chips and pour into crust. Top with spoonfuls of caramel and cut through top of cheesecake to swirl caramel. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Top should be cracked.

title: stuffed pistolettes
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add thawed broccoli (it's not necessary to cook first) and cheese.
Stir and heat until cheese is melted.
Make a pocket in each roll.
I slice them almost all the way through and then use a tablespoon to mash the bread inside to form a pocket.
You can pull some of the bread out if you wish. Bake at 375 until rolls are golden brown.

title: fried venison steak
directions: Marinate steaks in first 5 ingredients for 2 hours.
Take steaks out of marinade.
Dip in flour and salt.
Fry in hot oil until brown.
Add can of mushroom soup and water.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, vanilla and sugar until smooth. Fold in whipped topping.
Put into crust and cool in fridge until set.
Top with choice of toppings.
Keep in fridge.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Taken from Great-grandma Susie Jordan McDonald's journal given to daughter-in-law, Jessie Vee Jordan Justice.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean the mushrooms and remove the stems.
Set the caps aside. Mince the mushroom stems and mix the remaining ingredients. Stuff mixture into mushroom caps.
Broil 6-inches from heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until the tops are browned and mushrooms are heated through.

title: raspberry walnut torte
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, powdered sugar and butter.
Blend well. Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Drain raspberries, reserving juice for sauce.
Spoon berries over crust; sprinkle with walnuts.
Beat eggs with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and remaining flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour over walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown.
Cool and cut into squares. Serve with whipped cream and Raspberry Sauce.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix the cream cheese, margarine and flour.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients for the tart filling.
Roll cream cheese and flour mixture into small balls and press into small, greased muffin tins.
Add filling.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fudge cupcakes
directions: Combine brown sugar, milk and chocolate in a pan.
Stir over very low heat until chocolate melts; cool.
Gradually add 2/3 cup brown sugar to shortening, creaming until sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with 1/2 cup milk, beating after each addition.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Fill muffin cups in muffin pans 1/2 full. Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Stir together and place into a casserole dish.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Mix crushed crackers and oleo.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Whip together pudding, ice cream and milk.
Spoon on top of crust layer.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed Heath bars on very top.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil together margarine, sugar and syrup. Add baking soda. Pour hot syrup mixture over popcorn to coat evenly.
Bake at 250° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl; then add lard or Crisco.
Rub with tips of fingers until it feels like meal.
Add buttermilk, beating with a spoon.
Add just enough flour so the dough doesn't stick to your hands.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with small cutter; place on a lightly greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: easy brownies
directions: Measure and sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add melted butter, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool 5 minutes and frost.

title: biscuits
directions: Take flour, shortening and sugar; mix together until shortening is cut thorough flour, then add milk and mix with a heavy spoon.
Knead dough on a floured surface and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until tops are golden brown.

title: pizza
directions: Add yeast
to
mixture	of Crisco, sugar, egg and salt. Add a little milk to the yeast mixture.
Begin adding flour by 1/2 cup. Mix contents, adding milk and flour slowly until all the milk is used and you have used 3 cups flour.
If dough is still sticky, keep adding flour until the dough is smooth and forms a ball.
Let rise for at least 5 to 6 hours.

title: tuna-cabbage casserole
directions: Bring water to boil in medium saucepan.
Add chopped cabbage; cover and cook 1 or 2 minutes or until wilted; drain.
Arrange half of cabbage in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with tuna; cover with remaining cabbage.
Blend soup, milk, salt and caraway seed (optional).
Pour over ingredients in casserole.
Combine butter with bread crumbs and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until casserole is bubbly.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add to unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 425° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
For crispness, have pastry a little thicker than 1/8-inch.
Bake just until silver knife inserted 1 inch from side of filling comes out clean.
The center will set later.

title: pralines
directions: Cook sugar, water, salt and margarine to soft ball stage (236°).
Stir in pecans and remove from heat.
Beat until right consistency and drop onto waxed paper.
(Newspaper under waxed paper makes the pralines come up easily.) Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: alabama trash
directions: Mix pecans, coconut and powdered sugar.
Add margarine and condensed milk.
Mix thoroughly and chill overnight.
Melt chocolate over low heat in microwave.
Drop one ball at a time into the chocolate.
Make sure it is completely coated.
With a teaspoon, scoop ball up and drop on waxed paper.
Allow to cool.

title: egg business
directions: Prepare 1 day ahead.

title: stone soup
directions: Simmer water and stone.
Add ground beef.
Add clean sliced and diced vegetables.
Simmer until done.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Blend all ingredients well (except pecan) and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Mix pizza sauce with macaroni and hamburger.
Put in greased casserole, alternating layers with pepperoni and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Prepare pie shells; bake until light brown and set aside. Scrub sweet potatoes; boil in jackets approximately 30 minutes or until tender and drain.
Splash in cold water; peel.
In large mixing bowl, combine potatoes, margarine, milk, eggs, sugar, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat with mixer until smooth texture. Pour in prepared shells.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Work into a very smooth mixture. Shape into small balls.
Store, covered, in the refrigerator or freezer.
Makes 40 balls.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips, margarine and marshmallows, in large saucepan, over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat; mix in vanilla, coconut and oats thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper; chill until firm.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: sloppy toms
directions: Use your hands to break up ground turkey to put in skillet. Add onions.
Turn burner to medium-high.
Cook, stirring with a wooden spoon about 10 minutes, until all pink is out.
Drain fat (if any).
Stir tomato sauce, chili powder, mustard and Worcestershire sauce into meat mixture.
Cook on high until bubbly, stirring now and then, for 5 minutes.
Spoon meat mixture on bun and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Makes 8.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour at 350°. Can cover with crushed corn flakes.

title: christmas fruit balls
directions: Grind raisins, date, apricots, walnuts and lemon and orange rinds in food grinder or food processor very fine.
Mix well. Roll into bite-size balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator for at least 2 weeks to mellow flavors.
Before serving, you may want to coat again with confectioners sugar.
Makes 30 fruit balls.

title: pralines(microwave)
directions: In 4 or 5-quart glass dish, stir together buttermilk, sugar, pecans, salt and butter.
Cook on High 12 minutes, stirring every 4 minutes.
Take out of microwave.
Stir in baking soda until foamy.
Cook on High 1 minute.
This will give the pralines a caramel color.
Beat until tacky (stringy).
Drop by teaspoons on sheet of foil.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, salt and onion; let stand 2 hours.
Rinse and drain; set aside.
Boil together the sugar and vinegar.
Add turmeric and celery seed.
Pour mixture over cucumbers and freeze.

title: crock-pot chili with lamb
directions: Brown lamb in skillet.
Drain and pour 2 cups of boiling water over it to rinse; drain again.
Put lamb in crock-pot with all other ingredients and cook on low heat for 8 hours.
Delicious!

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix thoroughly as given.
Allow to blend 2 hours.
Very good for raw vegetable dip.
May also use on baked potatoes.

title: tangy red punch
directions: Melt red hots in 1 quart water.
Add pineapple juice and water to make 1 gallon.
Prior to serving, add ginger ale.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: small cheese cakes
directions: Soften cream cheese; add sugar and cream.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Put a liner in cupcake tins.
In each cup add one vanilla wafer.
Add mixture to about half full.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chunky beef over rice
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, broccoli and Worcestershire sauce. Over medium heat, heat through, stirring often.
Serve over rice. Makes 2 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Melt together the first 2 ingredients.
Remove from heat and add the sugar and eggs.
Beat
well and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 8 x 12-inch pan for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Moist and chewy.
Frost with your favorite frosting or dust with powdered sugar.

title: tea a la russe
directions: Make a good strong tea, to serve about 8 glasses.
Add juice of 4 oranges and 2 lemons; sweeten to taste and add cracked ice. Garnish with a few sprigs of mint.

title: rogene's oyster crackers
directions: Stir ingredients and oyster crackers.
Keep covered to store.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Halve chicken breasts.
Roll up and wrap with bacon slice. Place in baking dish lined with chipped beef (cut up).
Cover with soup and sour cream (mixed together).
Bake 3 hours at 275°.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Peel green rind off and all the pink of watermelon rinds. Soak rind in cold water for 24 hours.
(The white part cut off the rind.)
Drain and cover with clear water.
Add piece of alum.
Boil until rind is clear; drain.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and marshmallows together.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, combine juice, flour, sugar, egg and vinegar.
Cook until slightly thick.
When mixture is cool, combine with Cool Whip.
Fold in marshmallow mixture.
Add apples and peanuts. Sprinkle top with extra peanuts.

title: buck wheat cakes
directions: Make batter of first 3 ingredients with enough buttermilk to mix (not too thick).
Pour dissolved yeast cake into batter.
Let rise overnight.
Next, punch down and stir in soda and water. Stir in hard.
Pour onto hot, greased griddle.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Put into unbaked pie shell; cover with top crust and bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Blend butter, sugar, coconut, soda and vanilla.
Sift together baking powder and flour.
Add to butter mixture.
Roll into 1 inch balls or roll into 4 rolls and freeze.
Cut into 1/2 inch slices. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in sugar or sprinkle with colored sugar.
Good plain, too.

title: buttermilk yeast biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
This will keep for a week in refrigerator.
Take
out
as
much
dough as needed.
Roll out dough and cut.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Pour chopped nuts evenly over bottom.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over nuts.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: In a bowl, stir all ingredients except the last two.
Pour half the batter into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with chilies and cheese.
Pour remaining batter over all.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or just until set.
Serve warm with a spoon.

title: mom's lasagna
directions: Saute onion in oil in a saucepan.
Add ground beef and stir until crumbly; drain. Simmer together for 30 minutes the tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, pepper, sugar, oregano and garlic powder.
Add 2 cups water all to meat.
Cook the lasagna noodles according to directions on package.
Drain and place on wax paper on a tray. Combine Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and egg in a bowl.
Layer 1 cup ground beef sauce in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Alternate layers of noodles, beef sauce, cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven
for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: mediterranean-style roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray large shallow metal roasting pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut potatoes into 1-1/2 inch chunks; place in pan.
Drizzle 1 tablespoon oil over potatoes; toss to coat.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cut bell peppers into 1-1/2 inch chunks. Cut onion through core into 1/2-inch wedges.
Add bell peppers and onion to pan.
Drizzle remaining 1-1/2 teaspoons oil over vegetables; sprinkle with garlic, salt and black pepper.
Toss well to coat.
Return to oven; bake 18 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are browned and tender, stirring once.
Transfer to large serving bowl.
Drizzle vinegar over vegetables; toss to coat.
Add basil; toss again.
Serve warm or at room temperature with additional black pepper if desired.
Serves 6.

title: maple nut drops
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cream butter.
Add eggs, maple flavored syrup and maple flavoring; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually; mix thoroughly.
Add boiling water; mix well.
Stir in dates, pecans and shredded coconut.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
(I used parchment sheets.)
Bake in 350° oven for 13 to 16 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookie
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes after full boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Beat until mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls onto aluminum foil. Let cool.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Mix pie filling and pineapple in bottom.
In a bowl, melt butter in microwave.
Add cake mix and pecans and stir well.
Drizzle over cherries.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh fruit ice cream
directions: Pour chilled ingredients into ice cream maker can.
Proceed according to operating instructions.
For vanilla ice cream, simply omit fruit.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Boil and cool first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Add some nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350° or according to your own oven.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Mix pie filling and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat; add cola, pecans and pineapple.
Pour into 8-inch square pan and chill until firm. Beat Cool Whip and cream cheese in bowl until smooth.
Spread over gelatin.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pineapple.
Sift cake mix and put on top.
Pour melted margarine over top of this, then sprinkle coconut and nuts on top.
Bake at 325° until brown, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine with melted butter, salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients (except for cornflakes and butter).
Mix together lightly.
Put in buttered casserole.
May refrigerate overnight or bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Take out and top with buttered corn flakes.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: goulash done good
directions: Boil macaroni until done; drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef, bell pepper, garlic powder and onion in skillet; drain excess fat.
Combine meat mixture and macaroni, then add tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
You may wish to add additional chili powder.

title: chicken francaise
directions: Cut chicken breast into bite size pieces.
Shake in seasoned flour and saute until very lightly browned in pan with oil and butter combined.
Add pinches of oregano and sweet basil.
Spread pressed garlic cloves all over.
Mix and saute just a bit more. Continue process until all chicken has been sauteed.
Turn into a 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
Add mushrooms, chopped tomatoes and grated lemon rind.
Add squeeze Parkay in latticed pattern all over dish. Garlic and lemon juice should not overpower each other.
Cover dish with heavy-duty foil.
Can be frozen for later use.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: pumpkin fudge
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large saucepan. Bring to a boil. Boil for approximately 8 minutes (firm ball stage). Remove from heat and add cup melted white chocolate and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until firm (3 to 5 minutes).
Pour onto large platter; cut when cool.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and lard until consistency is like cornmeal.
Add water until moist.
Roll out on floured board.
Makes two crusts.

title: cheesy bread appetizer
directions: Melt margarine.
Add Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Slice bread almost all the way through in 1-inch slices.
Brush margarine on both sides of bread.
Slide a piece of Monterey Jack cheese into each bread crack.
Bake on aluminum foil for 10 minutes at 450°.

title: cowboy dinner
directions: Saute ground meat, onion, celery, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Add tomato soup, macaroni, kidney beans and Worcestershire sauce.

title: chocolate chip upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in microwave or on stove. Add brown sugar and stir well. Pour butter/brown sugar mixture into a well-greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle liberally with chocolate chips. Mix cake mix according to directions. Pour cake mix batter on top of chocolate chips. Bake according to package directions until toothpick comes out clean and sides are pulling away from pan. Remove from oven. Let set a few minutes and invert on serving dish. Elevate cake pan, letting icing settle on cake. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat peaches in saucepan until warm.
Preheat oven to 375°. Melt butter in oblong cake pan.
Mix flour, sugar and then milk. Pour dough mixture in pan, then peaches.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: ski slope spaghetti pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Boil spaghetti until tender.
Drain. Brown ground beef and drain.
Put spaghetti in large casserole dish.
Pour egg and milk over spaghetti.
Top evenly with 1 cup of cheese.
Bake for 7 minutes and remove.
Pour spaghetti sauce and ground beef over top.
Add rest of cheese.
Top with pepperoni. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove from oven and let stand for 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with French bread and salad.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Chill dough before rolling out, then roll out on lightly floured board.
Cut and place on cookie sheet that has been greased.
Bake until done at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Beat cream cheese and marshmallow cream together.
Add vanilla. Fold in grapes.
Dip will coat fruit.
Refrigerate and serve.
You can use this dressing for other fruits like strawberries, also.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: You need
one
flat
plate
or platter.
Spread refried beans on the
bottom.
Mix 1/4 of package of taco seasoning to sour cream.
Stir well.	Layer on top of refried beans.	Layer cheese, onions and black olives.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted oleo.
Sprinkle over bottom of 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish and press it down.
Mix softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and half of the Cool Whip.
Layer bananas, cream filling, then pineapple.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and garnish with maraschino cherries and chopped nuts.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms, remove and chop stems.
Reserve mushroom caps and 1/3 cup chopped stems.
Place reserved chopped mushroom stems, green onion and butter in a 1-quart microwavable casserole.
Cook uncovered 3 to 4 minutes at power level 10 or until onion is tender.
Stir twice.
Stir in bread crumbs and parsley flakes. Stuff each mushroom with bread mixture.
Arrange mushrooms in a circle on paper towel-lined paper plate.
Cover with wax paper and cook at power level 10 until hot.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: In small mixing bowl beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and red pepper.
Spread evenly in a 9-inch or 10-inch round dish or pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, green onion and green pepper.
Bake in a 350° oven for ten minutes. Top with cheese. Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Good for crackers and vegetables.

title: my favorite banana nut bread
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and bananas, mixing well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir into banana mixture just until all ingredients are moistened. Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Spoon batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours, until tests done. Yields: One loaf.

title: berry ice cubes
directions: Use any type of whole, ripe berries, such as blueberries, raspberries or blackberries (except strawberries).
Fill ice cube trays with 1 or 2 berries in each section.
Cover with water and freeze overnight.
Add to your favorite beverage as you would a regular ice cube for an extra special effect.

title: honey muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add milk.
Add beaten eggs to mixture.
Add to flour mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Turn batter into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: crustless fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Mix together and pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: ground venison burgers
directions: In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, lime juice, mustard and lime peel; cover and refrigerate until serving.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Put in loaf pan and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy jambalaya (microwave)
directions: Mix it all together in microsafe dish.
Cook covered on High for 2 minutes, then 30 minutes on Medium.

title: fruit salad(serves 10)
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges well, saving the juice.
Cook vanilla pudding in 3 cups of the saved fruit juice until thickened.
Combine thickened pudding mixture with pineapple chunks, oranges and cherries.
Don't save cherry juice.
Add as many sliced bananas as preferred.
Keeps good and serves approximately 10.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk for one hour.
Add beaten egg and brown sugar.
Mix and stir dry ingredients; then add these in liquid ingredients.
Add melted shortening, mixing well but do not beat too much.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 16.

title: peanut butter dreams
directions: Mix together margarine, graham crackers, peanut butter and powdered sugar until well blended.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Melt together chocolate chips and margarine.
Spread on top of chilled base.
Cut into bars.

title: winning sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oil and butter until fluffy.
Beat in eggs. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture along with vanilla; mix well.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Form into balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press flat with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cool coffee eggnog
directions: Advance preparation:
Stir milk into beaten egg yolks.
Add the 1/4 cup sugar, instant coffee granules, vanilla and salt. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats a metal spoon.
Chill mixture thoroughly.

title: funnel cake
directions: In 12-inch skillet, over medium heat, heat about 3/4-inch salad oil to 370°.
Mix, with a whisk, flour, milk, baking powder, salt and egg.
Hold a narrow spouted funnel (1/2-inch spout). Close spout with finger.
Pour scant 1/4 cup batter into funnel, over hot oil.
Carefully remove finger to let batter run out in a stream while making a circular movement about 6-inches in diameter.
Fry 6 to 8 minutes, until golden brown, turning with tongs.
Drain well on paper towel.
Repeat 6 times.
Stir well before pouring.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli in small pieces.
Dice onion and bacon and add to broccoli.
Add raisins.
In small bowl, mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Add to broccoli mix and let salad set 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tbsp. sugar in 13 x 9 inch pan and bake 8 minutes in a 400 degree oven.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Get 2 peanut butter cookies.
For each ice cream sandwich, press slightly rounded tablespoonful of ice cream between 2 cookies; place in small pan.
Freeze until firm.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Clean seeds out of jalapenos.
Cube 6 ounces Cheddar and 8 ounces Monterey Jack and put 1 cup of each into clean jalapeno. Mix 10 ounces grated cheese, sausage and Bisquick into a ball. Make golf ball sized and flatten.
Wrap around peppers.
Coat with beaten egg; roll in Shake 'n Bake.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut all biscuits into fourths.
Place 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a paper sack.
Add biscuit pieces, a few at a time, and shake to coat well.
Arrange sugar-coated biscuit pieces in a well-greased angel food cake pan.
(Do not use pan with sloping sides.)
Place 3/4 cup sugar, brown sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and margarine in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn upside down and remove from pan immediately.
Pick pieces off with toothpicks or fingers.
Real good with coffee.

title: cheese pops or straws
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour.
Blend in flour.
Knead. Form in long smooth roll 1-inch in diameter.
Cut in 1/4-inch slice.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes on 350°.
I use the star disc (No. 2) with the cookie press to shape the straws.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix whipped cream and marshmallows.
Refrigerate overnight. Add cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and oranges.
Drain pineapple, then add sliced grapes, etc.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8-inch pan in oven set at 375°. Meanwhile, in medium size mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Stir well.
Add vanilla and stir.
Gradually add milk, blending away any lumps.
Remove pan from oven when margarine is completely melted.
Pour batter into center of pan.
Do not stir. Spoon peaches into batter.
Sprinkle sugar over top of peaches. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes four servings.

title: billy's apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in mixing bowl.
Add sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Put into unbaked pie shell. Dot with butter.
Put top crust on top.
Put four slashes in crust to allow steam to escape.
Crimp edges.
Sprinkle a
little sugar on top.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in 375° oven.

title: pecan fried rice
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add rest of ingredients and heat through.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 11 x 14-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until well blended.
Add milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Put into ice cream bucket and fill the rest with fresh milk.

title: fresh vegetable rolls
directions: Heat oil in a skillet and saute vegetables for about 3 minutes. Set aside.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix butter, vanilla and
sugar	together and beat until fluffy.
Add flour and
pecans.
Roll into walnut-sized balls. Bake 30
to
minutes in 275° oven.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.	Cool and roll in powdered sugar again.

title: toasty peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place peaches in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of peaches.
Bake in a preheated oven approximately 30 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Serve warm or cold with cream, ice cream or whipping cream.
Serves 6.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Grease cake pans.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: bisquick noodles
directions: Work Bisquick into egg.
Roll and stretch dough until paper thin.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares or regular noodle strips.
Cover lightly with a towel and allow to dry at least 6 hours.
Drop into simmering broth or thin gravy.
Cover and cook gently about 15 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: white choco-chip cookies
directions: Beat butter until smooth.
Add sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add 1/4 at a time, beating until smooth.
Fold in coconut, nuts and chips.
Place on greased cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 5-8 minutes.

title: instant chocolate drink mix
directions: Mix together.
Take 1/3 cup mixture and add boiling water to make one cup.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in pan.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Add Chex and nuts.
Mix over low heat.
Heat in oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: greek beans
directions: Take an 8-quart kettle.
Wash beans with soda; rinse well. Put beans, onions, green pepper, carrots and chili peppers in kettle.
Fill 2 inches from top with cold water.
When the pot starts to boil, put tomatoes and oil in.
Cook on medium heat for 5 hours.
Serve with hot bread or French garlic bread.

title: stuffed apples
directions: Peel and core apples.
Boil until tender in enough water to cover.
Add lemon juice to water to prevent discoloration or add food coloring, if desired.
Drain.
Mix cream cheese, nuts and raisins.
Fill centers of apples with mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: peaches 'n cream pie
directions: Grease a 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Combine first 7 ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into prepared pan.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat all ingredients 5 minutes or until thickened.
Frost cake.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: *Substitute any type of fruit, such as fruit cocktail.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, butter, green onions and 1 c. cheese. Put in a greased 3 qt. casserole, gently stir in potatoes, salt and pepper.
Top with remaining cheese and cracker crumbs.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine berries and sugar; let stand 30 minutes.
Before serving, spoon 2/3 of berries on croissant bottoms.
Top with whipped topping, saving about 1/2 cup.
Replace tops and garnish with remaining berries and whipped topping.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Beat eggs.
Stir in flour and remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown and firm in center.
This pie makes its own crust and is delicious served warm.

title: american pie(8 servings)
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in large saucepan. Gradually whisk in milk until smooth.
Bring to boil, stirring gently, over medium-high heat.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks lightly in small bowl.
Gradually whisk in 1 cup hot mixture.
Return to saucepan, whisking constantly.
Return to boil and boil 1 minute more.
Remove from heat; whisk in lemon juice, butter, vanilla, lemon peel and nutmeg until completely smooth.
Cover surface; cool 15 minutes on wire rack.
Whisk in sour cream; pour into baked 9-inch pastry crust.
Cover filling; refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Just before serving, spread top with whipped cream.

title: beef and broccoli chowder
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in Dutch oven until beef is brown; drain. Stir in water, potatoes, sauce mix, carrots, mustard, salt and pepper. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in broccoli; cover and cook 10 minutes longer. Makes 8 cups.

title: scrumptious baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken (skin if wanted).
Put in bowl and sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Roll in self-rising flour.
Place in 9 x 13-inch foil-lined baking pan which has the foil buttered. Place small pats of margarine on chicken and place in oven for 15 minutes (no foil on top).
Mix the water and evaporated milk together and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer or until done.

title: cherry compote(freezable)
directions: Place cherries in pan.
Wash orange and grate rind into pan. Squeeze juice and stir into cherries.
Add honey and cinnamon, then add water (or wine); bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes until tender.
Remove from heat.
Cool. Freeze in rigid container.
Freezer life:
3 months.

title: quick chicken-n-dumplin's
directions: Cut chicken into chunks.
Boil.
In a large sauce pan, add chicken, soup, milk and water.
Heat to boiling point, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Pull apart biscuits into bite size pieces and add to soup mixture.
Heat and stir until dumplings reach desired texture.

title: georgia mud cake
directions: Cream together butter or margarine with the sugar in a large bowl of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and cocoa.
Slowly add to batter.
Add peanuts.
Bake for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
While cake is fresh from the oven and still warm, top with marshmallows. Ice with Georgia Mud Cake frosting.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and onion, then dice them up.
Cover with water and cook until done.
Add salt and pepper and celery seed.
Add stick of butter and milk.
Rinse out cans with water and add to soup.
Mix flour with water and add to the potatoes for a thicker soup.
When it comes to a boil, it is done.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown chops, drain off grease. Bring to a boil liquid and spice mixture. Reduce heat and cook 5 minutes. Remove and place chops in baking dish. Pour sauce over chops. Put a cover on, bake 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: 7-up fried pies
directions: Roll out biscuits and fill with pie filling. Boil the sugar, 7-Up, cinnamon and butter until it melts.
Grease pan.
Pour over pie.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Good with vanilla ice cream.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix together and cook at 325° for 4 hours in casserole dish. Stir every hour.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mexican fried rice
directions: Fry the rice with oil at medium temperature until it is brown. Add onions until soft.
Add tomato sauce.
Stir it up.
Add boiling water, salt and garlic powder for flavor.
Cook at low temperature for about 40 minutes until the rice is soft.

title: feta cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and butter.
Add Feta cheese, crumbled.
Add finely chopped black olives and green onion.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and oleo together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat egg whites, adding sugar.
Spread over crumbs and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Spread lemon pie filling over top. Top with Cool Whip.
Add nuts, if desired.
Chill 4 to 5 hours. (Can use chocolate or any other pudding.)

title: american persimmon pie
directions: Mix persimmon pulp, egg and milk.
Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch and add to first mixture.
Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry and pour in filling.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce temperature to 350° and bake 50 to 60 minutes longer. Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: champagne cup
directions: Sweet fruit juices with sugar to taste.
Combine all the ingredients.
Pour into a punch bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes with a large piece of ice.
Serves 20.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Drain and arrange stalks in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken on top.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Halve zucchini.
Scoop out centers, leaving 1/4-inch shell; place in shallow baking dish.
Coarsely chop zucchini centers; mix with next 8 ingredients.
Spoon into shells.
Top with sauce and cheese (if desired).
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4. Each serving = 3 protein (4 if you use cheese), 1 fat, free vegetables and optional calories for sauce.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix in bowl the corn and green pepper together.
In another bowl, beat eggs until thick.
Mix with corn and pepper.
In separate bowl, mix flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk; mix well.
Add to corn mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared ovenproof bowl and dot with butter.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: world's greatest home-burger
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Form into patties and place on grill pan.
Bake at 425° until done.
Serve on a bun with cheese, lettuce, tomato, pickle, onion, etc.

title: married woman cake
directions: Mix well with oil of sympathy.
Flavor with a bright fireside and a loving kiss.
Bake well all your life.

title: popovers
directions: In small deep mixing bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add flour, milk, melted margarine and salt. Beat just until blended: do not overbeat.
Pour batter into 8 to 12 well greased muffin cups.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 50 minutes or until puffed up and golden brown.
Makes 8 to 12 popovers.
Cool slightly. Cut open and serve with butter or margarine.

title: creamy oriental noodles
directions: Prepare noodles according to directions.
Drain water.
In saucepan mix soup, sour cream and flavor pack that came with noodles.
Place noodles on plate with beef or chicken and pour sauce over both.

title: beef casserole italiano
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in the tomato sauce, parsley, oregano, basil, pepper and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: prize peach cobbler
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder; mix with 1 cup sugar. Slowly stir in milk to make batter.
Melt butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour batter over melted butter; do not stir!
Mix the peaches and 1 cup sugar thoroughly and carefully spoon them over the batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot or cold with ice cream if desired.
Serves 6.

title: lite chicken and dumplings
directions: Roll the dough as flat as possible. Slice into strips.
Heat the broth to boiling.
Tear each strip of dough into several pieces, dropping them into the boiling broth. Reduce heat to a simmer.
Cover and allow to cook for about 6 minutes.
Remove cover.
Add chicken, black pepper, milk, and margarine.
Continue to cook until slightly thickened.
Makes 6 servings with less than 2 grams of fat per serving.

title: drive 'em wild potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out potatoes, leaving 1/8-inch shell.
Add sour cream and butter to potato mixture; mash well.
Stir in bacon and 2 tablespoons chives.
Add Mozzarella cheese; mix well.
Fill shells with mixture.
Sprinkle with Swiss cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining chives. Serves 12.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Bake for 35 minutes at 400°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix and beat first 3 ingredients until fluffy.
Fold in nuts, marshmallows and coconut.
Chill 1 hour.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and margarine.
Add lemon juice and lemon peel.
Stir in egg yolks and milk.
Fold in egg whites. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole.
Put casserole in pan with 1 inch water surrounding it.
Bakes at 325° for 1 hour.

title: custard pie
directions: Gradually stir milk into blended eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt. Add 1/2 cup milk before putting in oven.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mandarin pork chops
directions: In large skillet, brown chops in oil on both sides; remove from pan. In skillet, add remaining ingredients except orange segments and green pepper; cook and stir until slightly thickened. Add pork chops; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender. Add orange segments and green pepper; heat through.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook all chicken parts (keep broth).
Cook spaghetti.
Mix in large bowl mushroom soup, milk, chicken broth, onion and green pepper (red pepper if you want) and Velveeta cheese (cut up in small squares).
Add a little pepper and salt.
Mix all together; pour in long greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and a little brown on top.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar; beat well. Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine buttermilk and soda; stir well. Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add the walnuts.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold in batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pans before removing.

title: white mice
directions: Mix in order given until creamy.
Shape into crescents or ovals and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Do not brown.
Roll in 10x sugar when cool.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Place in blender on medium speed for 1 minute.
Pour enough marinade to just cover the meat into a Ziploc baggie.
Turn meat over several times.
Let marinate from 6 hours to 48.
Cook steak on grill.
Store the unused portion of marinade in the refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Chop fruits.
Crush crackers and wafers.
Mix together, adding orange juice.
Work with hands until thoroughly mixed.
Put in pan, pressing firmly.
Let stand several weeks.
Makes a large cake.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Simmer the first 7 ingredients together until broccoli is cooked.
In another pan, melt the margarine.
Add the flour; stir in the milk.
Bring to a slow boil, then add to broccoli mixture.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat sugars and eggs together.
Add pumpkin, oil and soda with water and stir. Add rest of ingredients and stir.
Pour into a greased bread pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: chocolate nut oat bars
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and oleo in bowl.
Mix well. Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs.
Spread remaining in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Pour milk over this.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Top with reserved crumbs.

title: bobbie's basic yellow cake(2 layers)
directions: Grease and flour 2 pans.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs. Add flour (sifted).
Add milk and vanilla.
Cook at 375° or 400° for about 20 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Can use any frosting with layers.

title: spinach bake(5 servings)
directions: In square baking dish, place 4 bread slices, 2 cheese slices, thawed spinach, pizza sauce, 2 cheese slices and 4 more bread slices.
Combine eggs, milk and salt and pour over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: angel salad
directions: Mix with spatula (do not use mixer) the Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip. Fold in pineapple, strawberries and pecans. Chill.

title: chicken salad with a twist
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on the package.
Mix the chicken and Italian dressing with hot macaroni; cool.
Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and mustard.
Stir in chopped onion, olive, cucumbers, celery and pepper.
Add to the macaroni mixture. Salt to taste.
Mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Sometimes I add some black or green seedless grapes and a small can of drained pineapple chunks to this recipe for color and a delightfully different taste.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large pan brown sausage and drain.
Combine all but milk and butter. Simmer until tender, then add milk and butter.
Simmer until hot and serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush 1/2 Oreo cookies and line bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, butter, Cool Whip and sugar in bowl.
In separate bowls mix pudding, vanilla and milk.
Blend both mixtures together and pour on top of crumbled cookies in pan.
(Use as a gag cake; put in flowerpot and add artificial flowers.)

title: lemonade pie
directions: Whip together in blender or with mixer and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Wrap chicken in foil and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour. Bone chicken and break into pieces.
Mix Soups, chili con carne, green chili salsa, milk, onion and olives.	Grease casserole.
Put layers of tortillas, chicken, sauce and cheese, about 2 or 3 layers.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12. May be made the day before.

title: italian chicken
directions: You will also need 1 cooking bag, 14 x 20-inch size.

title: chicken fruit nut salad
directions: On salad plate, arrange lettuce, chicken, apples and grapes. Drizzle dressing over salad.
Garnish with nuts.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Stew chicken, then use broth to cook 1 package rice.
Toast almonds in butter and salt under broiler in oven.
Mix remaining ingredients along with chicken and rice.
Place in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with slivered almonds.
(Almonds can be mixed in casserole if desired.) If not moist enough before baking, pour chicken broth over casserole.
This can be frozen, thawed well, then baked uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: old-fashioned nut loaf
directions: Cream the butter, gradually adding sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Repeat sifting and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended.
Gently stir in pecans and vanilla.
Spoon batter into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.

title: no-cal maple syrup
directions: Whisk together in a saucepan the first 4 ingredients. Bring to the boil. Stir in sweetener. Serve hot.

title: hashed turnip
directions: Peel turnip thickly and dice.
Cook until tender in boiling water, drain, return to saucepan.
Add butter, seasonings, parsley and cream.
Bring to boiling point and serve.
Serves about 4.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add beans, tomatoes and soup.
Layer Doritos and meat mixture and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave cheesy ham casserole
directions: Mix all except 1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon into
1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pickled beet salad
directions: Drain beets.
Place in a medium bowl.
Reserve juice in a saucepan.
Add vinegar and remaining ingredients to beet juice. Bring juice mixture to a boil.
Immediately remove from heat. Pour juice mixture over beets.
Cover and chill.
Drain beets before serving.
Serve Vidalia sliced onion.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: round red devil
directions: Soften cheese.
Blend in ham.
Refrigerate until firm.
Shape into about 30 small balls or 1 big cheese ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve on toothpick (if small balls).

title: lemon pudding
directions: Blend sugar, flour and salt to butter.
Add lemon juice and rind, blending well.
Mix egg yolks and milk.
Combine with sugar and lemon mixture.
Fold in egg whites and pour into buttered casserole (2-quart).
Place in pan of almost boiling water and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until golden on top.
Put Cool Whip on at serving time.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stack fruit cake
directions: Stew dried fruit with sugar (may need to add sugar to taste if 1 cup isn't enough) until tender.
Add spices and set aside to cool.

title: sorghum molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour.
Let stand 20 minutes, then add flour.
Roll into balls the size of a hickory nut.
Coat with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
