Cool and store in stone jar.

title: flo's marinated kiwi salad
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil; simmer for 3 minutes.
Stir in lemon peel, juice and rum; cool.
Pour lemon-rum syrup over kiwi fruit and melon balls; chill to marinate.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Bring water to boil.
Stir in Jell-O.
Add crushed pineapple, mashed bananas and strawberries (juice and berries).
Mix well. Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: four day coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to instructions.
Bake two layers. Let cool overnight, then separate two layers into four layers.

title: texas-style brisket
directions: You will need hickory smoking chips and a mop.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Combine sugar
and lemon juice with 4 cups water.
Boil for 5 minutes or until sugar is completely dissolved.
Remove from heat. Add
remaining
water and cool.
Just before serving, add
ice. Garnish with lemon slices and mint.
Yield: 25 servings.

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Arrange all ingredients in a large bowl.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender; drain well. Rinse under cold water and drain. Put into bowl. Dice up cucumbers and tomatoes. Add to spaghetti and pour in Italian dressing; mix well. Chill and serve.

title: chili con queso
directions: Line a strainer with a paper towel or coffee filter.
Spoon in yogurt and allow to drain up to 6 hours (I find 1 to 2 hours is usually enough).
Peel, seed and grate cucumber onto paper towels and allow to drain a few minutes.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add grated rind, nuts, dates, cranberries and 1 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Blend eggs, buttermilk and oil together and add to first mixture and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°. Cool in pan.
Mix together orange juice and 1 cup sugar and pour over cake in pan.
Cover pan with foil and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from pan and serve.

title: wedding soup
directions: Put broth on; add spinach and Parmesan cheese, enough to cover top of soup.
Stir and cook with lid on.
While this is cooking, make meat balls.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix in large bowl cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Add oil and milk and stir until well blended.
Add onion, peppers, cheese and corn.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13 1/2-inch glass baking dish that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn and eggs together.
Combine sugar, arrowroot, Season-All, dry mustard, onion and pepper.
Stir into corn mixture. Add milk and butter; stir well.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, celery, onion, green pepper, pimento and salt. Blend soup with milk, heat through and add cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into a 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: snack biscuit donuts
directions: Take each
biscuit
and
cut with a donut cutter.
Drop donuts and
holes in hot cooking oil and deep fry until golden brown, about 2
or 3 minutes.
Remove and lay on a paper towel to drain.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch pan. Put half of mixture in pan and sprinkle with half of frosting; repeat.
Pat with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: one dish meal(rice-broccoli-chicken casserole)
directions: Layer in casserole in order given.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 generously.

title: sinful french silk pie
directions: Beat butter and sugar until well blended, approximately 6 to 8 minutes, until mixture turns pale yellow.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in 1 egg at a time (approximately 3 minutes for each egg) on medium speed.
Fill pie shell and refrigerate.

title: georgia's apple souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Add marshmallows and brown.

title: happiness bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Turn down television.
Remove toys from countertop.
Measure 2 cups of flour.
Put flour, baking powder and salt into sifter.
Vacuum mixture from flour, which Benjamin spilled.
Get an egg.
Answer phone.
Grease pan.
Answer door. Take 1/2-inch of salt from greased pan and look for Benjamin.
Put mess in wastebasket.
Wash dishes.
Call the bakery and take an aspirin.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together; beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Beat in lemon extract and 7-Up by hand.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured large Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: chocolate supreme
directions: Mix together and spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook for 15 minutes.
Will be very hot.
Take from burner. Add 1 can medium size orange Jell-O.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: happy-times punch
directions: Combine frozen concentrates and water.
Place sherbet and ice cream in bottom of punch bowl.
Break in small pieces with large spoon.
Add juices.
Stir until sherbet and ice cream are partially melted.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix juices and water.
Chill.
Use some to make ice ring.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.
Pour into punch bowl. Gently drop in ice ring.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add baking soda and vanilla; mix well.
Pour over popcorn, stirring well to cover.
Place in a well-greased roasting pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and break up.

title: marvelous mix
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave. Pour over other ingredients; mix until well coated. Pour out on cookie sheet. Break into bite size pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: jello salad(weight watchers)
directions: Heat pineapple (with juice) to boiling.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool.
Fold in buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Pour into oblong Pyrex dish and chill.
Serves 10. (27 optional calories, 1/2 fruit exchange.)

title: linguini
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
In separate pot cook carrots and broccoli.
Drain about 1/2 of the water from pot.
Stir into the spaghetti the carrots, broccoli and remaining water.
Add Velveeta to liking.
Serve hot.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: Heat oil in a wok or large skillet. Add remaining ingredients; cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until cabbage is crisp-tender. Yields 8 servings.

title: husbands delight
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
First, put a layer of cooked noodles (about 1/2) in baking dish.
Then add all of the sauce.
Next, put the cheese mixture (cream cheese and sour cream) on top of the sauce.
Add the rest of the noodles and then cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: herbed chicken and vegetables
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken pieces.
Mix flour, basil, oregano, paprika, marjoram and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.

title: candy cereal treats
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Combine the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda; gradually add to the creamed mixture until mixture resembles coarse crumbs (do not overmix).

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Sprinkle tortillas with flour and cut into squares.
Bring chicken broth to a boil and drop tortilla pieces into the broth and cook 17 minutes.
Add chicken and evaporated milk. Heat thoroughly.

title: caramel bubble ring
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Melt butter.
Pull bread sticks apart.
Cut pinwheels in half.
Sprinkle 1/2 of pecans into Bundt cake pan.
Dip bread stick pieces into the butter and then roll in cinnamon/sugar.
Drop into pan.
Top with remaining pecans.
Mix caramel and syrup.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: cheesy rice and broccoli
directions: Bring broccoli and water to boil in medium saucepan, separating broccoli with fork.
Stir in Velveeta cheese, reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in rice; cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: dijon salad dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a small bowl and serve over salad.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender and debone.
Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soups and milk and pour over chicken.
Mix broth with stuffing mix and place on top of chicken and soup. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix 7-Up, sugar and cornstarch and cook in saucepan until thick. Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water. Add to cooked mixture and cool.
Add thawed strawberries.
Pour into pie shell and chill until set.
Cover with whipped cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put hash brown potatoes in large mixing bowl.
Pour melted butter over potatoes.
Mix in 1 can soup, grated cheese and sour cream.
Stir all together and place in buttered casserole dish. Top with buttered bread crumbs or potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: quick broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as instructed. Saute onion in bacon drippings. Mix all other ingredients together using hot rice to melt cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Make instant potatoes according to package directions. Mix sour cream and cream cheese together, then add to potatoes. Mix all other ingredients and pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: double decker knox blox
directions: In a large bowl, combine gelatine and Jell-O.
Add boiling water and stir until completely dissolved.
Add Cool Whip; stir well.
Pour into shallow baking pan (about 9 x 13-inches).
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1 inch squares.
Makes approximately 100 squares.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and spices together with a mixer to beat the oil and vinegar in the soup to make smooth dressing. Drain the cooked carrots, the dressing can be poured over the warm carrots.
Add the onion and green pepper last to keep the pepper more crisp.
Toss all together lightly.
Cover and refrigerate at least over night.
These will keep in the refrigerator a couple of weeks.

title: broccoli sausage quiche
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Place broccoli and sausage in bottom of 2 pie crusts.
Mix evaporated milk, water, eggs and milk together; set aside.
Combine flour, cheeses, salt and pepper and put over sausage.
Pour in milk-egg mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until browned at 350°.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Add these ingredients to eggs and sugar; cook slightly, stirring constantly.
Add 1 tablespoon vanilla and one No. 3 can peaches.
Pour mixture and mashed up peaches, including juice, into freezer can.
Finish filling to 3/4 full with regular milk. Freeze.

title: corn griddle cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and pepper.
Combine egg, milk and corn.
Add to flour mixture with shortening, mixing just until flour is dampened.
Bake on hot greased griddle.
Serve with butter and syrup.
Makes 12 to 15 griddle cakes.
Use can of luncheon meat and a citrus salad to complete meal.

title: double boiler frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in top of double boiler. Place over boiling water; beat with beaters until stiff peaks form. Scrape sides and bottom of pan occasionally. Fold in vanilla.

title: quiche cubes
directions: Coat a 1 quart baking dish with Pam.
Sprinkle cheeses, basil and turkey ham into dish.
Stir gently to mix.
Beat together eggs, egg white and milk.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Stirring until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firmly set.
Cut into 1 inch cubes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chewy cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together; gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and beat well; stir in pecans.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Foil line cookie sheet. Spread crackers on cookie sheet. Sprinkle chopped pecans on crackers. Combine butter and sugar. Boil for 3 minutes. Pour over crackers. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: layered tostado dip
directions: Combine beans and chili powder; mix well. Combine avocados, salad dressing, bacon, onion and seasoning. Mix well. Layer bean mixture, avocado mixture, olives, tomatoes, chilies and cheese in shallow bowl. Serve with tortilla chips. The avocado mixture can be served alone or as a dip or topping for Mexican dishes.

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Empty large container of plain nonfat yogurt into cheese cloth. Tie to kitchen faucet and drain overnight.
Season with snipped fresh herbs.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Stir sugar, milk, eggs, spices and pumpkin together; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.

title: chocolate custard bread pudding
directions: Add chocolate to milk; heat in double boiler.
When chocolate is melted, stir until blended.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and salt gradually, then add chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Place bread in greased baking dish.
Pour mixture over it; let stand 10 minutes.
Mix well before baking.
Place dish in hot water.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 minutes, or until pudding is firm.

title: zele's oyster stew
directions: Put juice from oysters, onion (cut fine) and soup in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Drop in oysters.
Let cook until oysters curl. Serve.

title: oatmeal superchip cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together. Sift baking soda, salt and flour together. Then add to creamed mixture along with the oatmeal and then the chips. Make round balls; flatten. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute.

title: banana split pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar in mixing bowl; blend well. Strain the juice off the pineapple. In pie crust layer cream cheese and sugar mixture. Top with sliced bananas. Top with crushed pineapple. Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with pecans. Cool in fridge before serving.

title: aunt margie's shrimp(can be used for appetizer or part of a meal)
directions: Cut bacon into two pieces and cross.
Place raw shrimp on center.
Place tomato wedge, onion wedge and 1 slice of jalapeno pepper on top of shrimp.
Fold up ends of bacon to cover all ingredients and secure with toothpicks (wooden ones).
Place in shallow dish and marinate with Dale's sauce.
Place in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes (not much longer).
Place on grill and cook until bacon is done.
Be careful as bacon has a tendency to catch fire if grill is too hot!

title: matzo stuffing
directions: Add salt, pepper, paprika, poultry seasoning, celery (water chestnuts can be substituted for celery) and parsley flakes to matzo.
Mix in eggs.
Brown onions in a large frying pan.
Add all ingredients to pan and fry together until light brown.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar and beat in the egg.	Add the milk gradually.	Cook
in
a double boiler until thick.	Add a piece of butter
the
size of an egg and let cool.
When cool, add vinegar to taste.

title: amalgamation cake
directions: Grind raisins and nuts together.
Mix in order given.
Bake in 8-inch round pans.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Separate and unroll breadsticks.
Put pepperoni slices over end half.
Fold other half over; seal end and twist.
Place on cookie sheet.
Combine cheese and seasonings and sprinkle on breadsticks. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with sauce.

title: lemon tart with almond crust(makes one 9-inch tart)
directions: Process first four ingredients in processor fitted with steel blade until they resemble coarse sand.
Pulse in butter and extract until butter is the size of peas.
Add ice water; pulse to incorporate (add more water, 1 tablespoon at a time, if dough seems dry).
Dump dough onto a sheet of plastic wrap; form into a disk.
Wrap and chill for at least 30 minutes before rolling out.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs or crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut steak into strips and fry in oil with onion.
Add water, salt, pepper and soy sauce; simmer 10 minutes.
Add celery.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add bean sprouts and cornstarch diluted with some water.
Heat through and serve over chop suey noodles or sprinkle on top.

title: ritz chicken
directions: Cook chicken; place in dish and add sour cream and soup that have been mixed together.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Butter a
x
13-inch pan.
Pour cream of chicken and cream of celery soup, water and rice into pan.
Stir to blend. Place chicken on top of rice mixture and sprinkle Lipton onion soup mix over
chicken.
Cover
pan
with aluminum foil.
Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Cook ingredients until slightly thickened.
Pour into pie shell and dot with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes; lower heat to 350° and bake for 20 to 30 more minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Alternate layers of tomatoes and onions (2 layers) in pie shell.
Season to taste.
Spread mixture of mayo and cheese on tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stroganoff easy
directions: Lightly mix ground beef, salt, pepper, garlic, bread crumbs and milk. Shape into small balls and brown in hot oil. Lift from frypan and pour off grease. Using the same pan, add sour cream, bouillon and onion soup and stir to mix. Return browned balls to this mixture and simmer (do not boil) until heated through. Serve on noodles, spaghetti or rice.

title: potato pierogi
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
The less you handle the dough, the more tender it will be.
Yields 2 dozen, depending upon size.

title: sugar "christmas" cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together well.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Chill dough well overnight.
Roll to desired thickness; cut into designs.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes (check bottoms).
Frost and decorate.
Makes lots!

title: fudge sauce for ice cream
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients in saucepan for two minutes.
Remove from heat, add last three ingredients and mix well.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine egg, pepper, salt and half the melted margarine.
Stir into squash and onion.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Pour remaining margarine over the top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix together and heat:
cheese, soup, butter, celery, and onion until butter is melted.
Add broccoli and rice.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: dandelion with hot dressing
directions: Fry up some bacon for taste and set aside.

title: pet-ritz easy caramel apple pie
directions: Cut caramel candies into 4 pieces, combine with flour. Add chopped apples, ice cream topping and lemon juice; mix well.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese in a mixer, then combine other ingredients and cover with chopped pecans.

title: zucchini-tomato sauce
directions: Saute onion, garlic and zucchini in oil in a medium saucepan until soft; stir in tomatoes, basil, salt, pepper and sugar.
Heat to bubbling; simmer 30 minutes or until sauce thickens slightly. Serve over fettucelle or spaghetti.
Yield:
3 cups.

title: teatime tassies
directions: Cheese Pastry:
Let cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter soften at room temperature, blend.
Stir in flour.
Chill slightly; about 1 hour or longer.
Shape in 2 dozen 1-inch balls.
Place in ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin cups.
Press dough on bottom and sides of cups.

title: cheesy ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare sauce mix, noodles and broccoli according to package directions.
(If fresh broccoli is used, cook as usual.)
Drain noodles and return to pan.
Add sauce, pepper, milk, ham, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and broccoli.
Mix.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake, covered, in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Place dry ingredients in bowl.
Combine eggs and buttermilk. Stir into flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add shortening. Bake on hot griddle.
Makes about 18 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: pie crust
directions: Use a fork to mix together the flour and Crisco; set aside. Mix together the next 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Combine all together and refrigerate.
Roll out and use for pies.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Make cookies.
When dough is shaped into balls, roll in granulated sugar.
Place on cookie sheet (do not flatten).
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pink or green punch
directions: Mix sugar, Kool-Aid and water.
Can be done at night before refrigerated.
Pour Kool-Aid in the punch bowl.
Add frozen lemonade, partially thawed, and pineapple juice.
Mix all together and add ginger ale.
If punch taste is strong, add more ginger ale.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Put cake mix, flour and jello into mixing bowl; blend well. Add oil, milk and strawberries.
Add flour and eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Bake in two 9-inch pans for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine the first five ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrots.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Add pepper, onion, yellow squash and zucchini.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms; cover and simmer 5 more minutes. Drain.
Place vegetables in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil just until cheese melts. Yields 8 servings.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Saute pepper, onion and hot dogs until lightly browned.
Stir in remaining items. Bring to boil.
Cover lightly and simmer 10 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix the pineapple, cottage cheese and Cool Whip well.
Fold in the orange jello.

title: chocolate-oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and lay butter on top.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Beat in eggs, sugars and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, cocoa and salt.
When mixed well, put in a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When baked, spread with topping.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together except the butter and crackers.
Crush 1 package crackers and sprinkle on top. Cut up the butter over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: very easy rolls
directions: Cream sugar, salt and Crisco; add boiling water.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add eggs and stir.
Add yeast to mixture. With spoon, blend in flour.
Refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours.
Roll, shape and let rise in warm place about an hour.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Use what you need, because they will hold in refrigerator for weeks.
Enjoy!

title: baked pork tenderloin
directions: Season flour with salt and pepper.
Rub both sides of roast with flour mixture, then brown in butter.
Place in oven serving dish.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of fat.
Brown onion and garlic, then stir in ginger.
Mix together applesauce, wine and soy sauce; stir into onion mixture.
Simmer 1 minute, then pour over pork.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable pasta stir-fry
directions: Cook linguine in boiling, unsalted water; drain and keep warm. Preheat a wok or large skillet over high heat; add olive oil (add more oil, if necessary, during cooking).
Stir-fry garlic in hot oil for 15 seconds.
Add carrots; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add zucchini, onion and celery; stir-fry about 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Gently stir in garbanzo beans, tomatoes, olives, snipped parsley and basil.
Cover and cook for 1 to 2 minutes or until mixture is heated through.
Remove the wok or skillet from heat.
Add linguine, Parmesan cheese and margarine.
Toss gently until mixture is coated.
Transfer to 4 dinner plates; sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over each serving. Garnish with fresh basil, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: bacon cheddar dip
directions: Mix all together. Serve with snack crackers or toasted bread slices. Yield: About 2 cups.

title: reese's balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and sugar. Roll into balls and refrigerate. Melt chocolate in double boiler; dip ball in chocolate. Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crushed crackers.
Place half of crumbs in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over crumbs.
Put remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: orange vanilla shake
directions: Peel and cut up oranges and add the vanilla ice milk.
Mix in blender or food processor until smooth.
Serve.

title: teriyaki
directions: Mix soy sauce, honey, lemon juice and garlic in bowl.
Add thinly sliced beef and let stand 15 minutes.
Place oil in pan and heat.
When hot, add steak with sauce.
Cook until all juice is gone.

title: quiche
directions: Drop zucchini slices in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Saute onion.
Combine all ingredients; pour into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 450° and 15 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: corn chowder
directions: Boil diced potatoes in 1 pint of water for 15 minutes.
Saute onion with salt pork or bacon for 2 minutes.
Add to potatoes and corn.
Continue cooking until potatoes are done.
Add 1 pint milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat to boiling and serve at once.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together and put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt one 8-ounce Hershey bar in double boiler.
Pour over mixture and let cool.

title: granny's chocolate icing
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Boil hard 1 minute.
Remove from heat and beat a few minutes until fluffy.

title: herb dressing
directions: Blend well and serve over mixed greens.
Yields 1 pint.

title: rainbow cookies
directions: Put the butter, sugar and vanilla in a bowl. Beat with an electric mixer until creamy. Add the flour. Beat with the mixer for several minutes until a smooth dough forms. Divide the dough into 7 pieces. Put each piece in a separate bowl. Add several drops of food coloring to each bowl. Make each piece of dough a different color: red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo (dark blue) and violet. Work the color into each piece of dough with your hands. Then roll each piece of dough into a ball. Now press all the dough balls together. Roll them into a log. The log should be about 8 inches long. Chill the log in the refrigerator for 15 minutes. Slice the log into pieces. Each slice should be about 1/4 inch thick. Put the slices on a cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: honey pecan pie
directions: Beat
eggs
well;
add honey, vanilla, butter and salt. Line bottom
of
pie
shell
with pecans and pour mixture over pecans. Bake 10 minutes at 450°, lower to 325° and bake until knife comes out clean (30 to 40 minutes).

title: maple cream coffee treat
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, combine first four ingredients.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth; stir in coconut.

title: red-eye gravy
directions: Cook steak tender in 2 tablespoons drippings.
Mix the ingredients and rub on each side of the uncooked steak.
Add ham to skillet with 2 tablespoons of drippings; cook until brown, about 2 minutes each side.
Transfer to platter and keep warm. Add you 1 cup coffee to skillet and cook until syrupy, about 5 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add flour and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and pour in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and onions.
Chop fine.
Cook until soft.
Add red pepper and spices.
Cook over medium heat until half the original amount.
Fill jars and seal.

title: peasant salad
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, cut tomatoes, cucumbers, yellow pepper and red onion into bite-sized pieces. Place vegetables in large bowl.
Stir in chopped basil leaves, capers, garlic, olive oil, red wine vinegar, salt and pepper.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Rinse whole cranberries in running water.
Cut oranges in quarters. Put cranberries and oranges through food grinder.
Stir in sugar and refrigerate up to two days before you plan on using the relish.
Makes 2 cups of relish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add chopped onion; turn
off stove and let stand on stove.
Add crumbled cornbread, cooked and mashed squash, 2
beaten
eggs,
cream of mushroom
soup
and
onion margarine mixture.
Salt and pepper.
Bake in
quart casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and mix in eggs, Parmesan cheese and butter.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown beef, onion and green pepper; drain and pour over spaghetti.
Cover all with sauce.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with cheese, last 15 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: michelle's favorite barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together by hand.

title: oslo twists
directions: Heat deep fat to 375°.
Beat egg yolks, egg and salt together until very stiff (about 10 minutes).
Blend in confectioners sugar and flavoring, thoroughly.
Add flour, all at once; mix well.
Turn dough onto well-floured cloth-covered board.
Knead until surface of dough is blistered in appearance (about 7 minutes).
Divide dough in halves and roll out each half very thin.
With pastry wheel or knife, cut dough into diamonds or rectangles about 4 x 2-inches.
Make a 1 inch slit in center of each; draw a long point of diamond through slit and curl back in opposite direction.
Fry until delicately browned in deep hot fat about 1/2 minute on each side.
Turn quickly and brown other side.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar just before serving. Makes 2 or 3 dozen.

title: bellingham float(pudding cake)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, cut in shortening, add milk, vanilla and nuts.
Pour batter into greased pan.

title: apple cinnamon dumplings
directions: Sift flour and salt into a bowl.
Add shortening and cut it in with 2 knives or a pastry blender until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle in the water.
Mix lightly.
Turn out onto a pastry board and shape in a ball.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick into an 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cut into 6-inch squares.
Peel apples and core.
Place in center of pastry square.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Pour into center of each apple.
Pat with oleo.
Bring points over apples and press edges together.
Brush surface with milk.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until apple is tender.

title: alma's summer salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; add remaining ingredients to macaroni and blend well.

title: lemonade surprise
directions: Beat the lemonade with the can of milk for approximately 3 minutes.
Fold in one tub of Cool Whip.
Pour into cooled pie shell and refrigerate.
Before serving cover the top with Cool Whip.

title: summer pizza
directions: Press rolls in rectangular cake pan. Bake according to directions. Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing to taste. Spread over baked rolls. Top with vegetables and Cheddar cheese.

title: oven crisped potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into eighths or sixteenths.
Brush margarine or spray with Pam evenly on potatoes to coat.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Roast potatoes in 450° oven until brown and crispy, approximately 20 to 30 minutes, turning once or twice.
Stir in basil and shallots.
Transfer to serving dish.

title: soul food
directions: Cut up enough bacon to line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Wash vegetables and cut up to desired size with skin.
Can also add green chilies.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix in bowl.
Then put in dish and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.
When done, add cheese. Melt and serve.
If you choose to layer the vegetables, add salt, pepper and butter between layers.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Cool and dice.
Mix chicken with sour cream and tomatoes.
Line 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with 2 tortillas, layer with chicken mixture and sprinkle on cheese.
Layer twice more, ending with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate mint squares
directions: Bottom layer:
Heat 1/2 cup of butter and 1/2 cup of cocoa in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 cup confectioners sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs; mix well. Press into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.

title: pig cake
directions: Blend together cake mix, butter, vanilla and orange juice until smooth.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Beat mixture 4 minutes at high speed.
Drain oranges and crush.
Add to mixture, beating only enough to mix oranges.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: german style chicken and corn
directions: Cook
and
debone
chicken.
Put broth	in
heavy
pot. Bring to a boil and add corn.
Stir to keep from sticking.
If corn gets too
thick, add some water.
When corn is done, add chicken and serve
hot.
It
is best when you use fresh field corn.
Butter and bacon
drippings
are optional, but if used, add while corn is cooking.

title: beef supreme
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery; pour off excess fat.
Add pepper, tomato sauce, soups and rice or noodles.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add sugar, lemon and pineapple juice.
Stir to dissolve.
Chill until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients; chill until firm.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop mix by tablespoon into 1/8-inch hot oil in large skillet.
Flatten patties to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cook to golden brown.
Turn and brown on the other side.

title: 5 "p" salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on package, add all ingredients and let gel.
Cut into small squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
Add a teaspoon of mayonnaise on each individual serving.

title: snack pretzels
directions: Mix in bowl.
Set for 2 hours.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: cucumber slices
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature and mix in the package of dry Italian salad dressing.
Spread on small slices of cocktail rye bread and top with a thin slice of cucumber.
Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine margarine, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixing bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chocolate chips and nuts (batter will be stiff).
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Place broccoli in microwave and cook on High in package for 15 minutes.
Saute onions in butter.
When broccoli is done, add butter, onions, Cheez Whiz, rice and soup.
Stir until mixed. Stick back in microwave for 3 minutes.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Peel and cut oranges into small pieces.
Core and cut apples into small pieces.
Slice grapes into two pieces.
Peel and cut bananas into small pieces.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Put into a covered container and chill overnight.

title: spiced chicken wings
directions: Remove tips from wings.
Wash wings with cold water.
Place in shallow baking pan in single layer.
In saucepan, blend other ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Pour over chicken wings.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Turn wings several times during baking.

title: chicken rigatoni
directions: Brown chicken breasts in pressure cooker in butter; remove. Combine tomato sauce, chicken bouillon, oregano, garlic salt, onion salt and salt and pepper to taste; bring to a boil.
Place chicken in sauce.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
While chicken is cooking, boil rigatoni noodles.
(Noodles are done when they flatten out.)
After cooking noodles, rinse under cold water. Remove chicken from tomato sauce, place on a serving dish.
Run noodles under hot water and add to tomato sauce.
Chicken breasts are served alongside the noodles.

title: hot potato wurst salad
directions: Place potatoes in 1-inch boiling water; cover and cook just until tender when pierced (about 30 minutes).
Drain.
When cool, peel and slice potatoes.
Set aside.
Remove casings and cut wurst into 1/2-inch slices.

title: chicken creole with chile cream sauce
directions: Season chicken with Creole seasoning.
Heat oil in skillet. Add chicken and cook until browned.
Add soup, water, chiles and lime juice.
Heat to a boil.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, rice, sugar and vanilla; put in casserole.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Fifteen minutes before done, stir in raisins; sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: easy ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: ham-egg brunch
directions: Place buttered bread in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put shaved ham and grated cheese on top.
Beat eggs and milk; pour on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated mushrooms and artichoke hearts
directions: Mix water, wine vinegar and oil.
Add spices and shake thoroughly.
Pour over mushrooms and artichoke hearts.
Seal and place in refrigerator, turning often.
Great if marinated for 3 days, excellent if marinated even longer.

title: chicken livers paste
directions: Put oil in pan.
Add livers, onions and add spices to pan. Season to taste.
Grind up livers when cooked, add ground eggs to livers and mix.
This recipe is for 30 livers, 8 eggs and 6 large onions.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In a medium bowl, combine soup, chilies, red bell pepper and sour cream.
Whisk to blend well.
Separate and set aside 1 cup. Mix chicken into remaining mixture in bowl.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of mixture at one end of each tortilla.
Sprinkle each with about 1 tablespoon of cheese.
Roll up and arrange in a shallow baking dish just large enough to hold enchiladas in a single layer.
Pour remaining cup of sour cream mixture over enchiladas.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Place in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until hot and crispy.
Can be microwaved in a covered dish with waxed paper.
Cook on Medium 7 to 10 minutes, until heated through.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook the first three ingredients together until meat is brown. Pour into Dutch
oven.
Add
remaining ingredients and simmer for two hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in buttered shallow baking dish (about 2-quart capacity).
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix butter and vanilla and add to flour mixture, tossing with a fork to make a crumbly mixture.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown and apples are tender.
Let cool partially, then top with cream.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: pecan turtle bars
directions: Combine flour, 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup softened butter in a large bowl. Beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Pat mixture evenly onto bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle pecans over crumb mixture.

Combine 2/3 cup butter and remaining 1/2 cup brown sugar in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly. Pour into pan, spreading evenly over crust. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes until chocolate melts.
Use knife to swirl chocolate.
Makes 48 bars.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet until crisp.

Remove and set aside. Drain, leaving only about 2 to 3 tablespoons of drippings. Cook onion until tender. Stir in flour and blend well. Add vinegar and water. Cook and stir until bubbly and slightly thickened.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Crumble bacon gently. Stir in bacon and potato slices to lightly coat. Serve warm. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: amish bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and butter.
Stir until butter is melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Combine eggs, sugar, salt and nutmeg; beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Stir in milk mixture.
Place bread crumbs in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with raisins. Add milk mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set. Serve warm.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice and soy sauce.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Add onions, celery, water chestnuts, sprouts, salt, pepper and mushroom soup.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Turn into a greased casserole pan and sprinkle a few noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly. Serve
with
the rest of the noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave caramel turtles
directions: Place caramels, milk and butter in 1-quart microwave-safe measuring cup.
Heat in microwave on Medium-high for 4 to 5 minutes or until melted.
Spray a cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Arrange pecans in 3's on sheet.
Spoon 1 tablespoon melted caramel over pecans to cover.
Refrigerate, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Place chocolate morsels in 2-quart measuring cup and microwave for 5 to 6 minutes on Medium-high until melted.
Spoon over caramels.
Allow to cool.
Refrigerate in covered container. Enjoy!

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and stem strawberries; put in graham cracker crust.
Mix together all other ingredients in pot and bring to a boil. Cook and stir about 5 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour mixture over strawberries.
Let congeal in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip as serving.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs until done.
Peel and cool.
Place cooled eggs in large jar.
Cover with peppers and vinegar.
Ready to eat in 5 to 6 days.

title: combination baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and place in a large Dutch oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper in a large skillet until beef is browned, stirring to crumble; drain. Stir in tomato soup and remaining ingredients; simmer 10 - 15 minutes stirring mixture often. Server on toasted buns.

title: chicken morfasso
directions: Combine eggs, half and half, and Parmesan cheese in bowl; set aside.
Coat chicken breasts with flour; shake off excess.
Heat oil until haze forms (use large skillet).
Whisk egg mixture and dip breasts to coat evenly.
Add chicken to skillet, then reduce heat to low and saute slowly until golden brown, turning occasionally to cook evenly.
Remove to heated platter and keep warm in 200° oven.

title: country ham
directions: Make
dough
out
of
flour, cinnamon, mustard, cloves, black pepper and brown sugar.
Add enough water to make stiff dough. Cut
skin
from
ham.
Place
in
roaster fat side up. Spread the dough
over
the
fat side of ham and seal next to pan.
Bake uncovered
in 350° oven for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Ham is
done
if bone moves easily.
Discard crust and remove ham immediately from grease.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cousin ella bess' coffee cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients twice.
Add egg, oil and milk to sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° until brown around edges.

title: nuts and bolts(a christmas snack)
directions: Mix pretzels, Cheerios, both Chex cereals and nuts well.
Pour over this a mixture of the butter, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and garlic.
Mix well.

title: pizza bread
directions: Roll out bread dough on floured surface.
Layer cheese, pepperoni, ham and salami.
Roll back up into a loaf. The loaf will be somewhat lumpy.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for about 40 minutes. Slice and serve. Makes about 8 slices.

title: miss daisey's casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add celery, green pepper and onions and saute.
Add tomato juice, tomatoes and everything except Cheddar cheese.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour into 2 casserole dishes. Bake for 30 minutes.
Add Cheddar cheese on top.

title: pork chop dinner in a skillet
directions: Place pork roast on heavy foil.
Cover with Lipton dry onion soup mix.
Fold foil airtight around meat.
Bake at 350° for few hours (about 3 hours).

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Cook until thick, cornstarch, sugar and milk.
Add vanilla and margarine and stir.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chick-n-potato(light meal for one)
directions: Bake potato in microwave for 8 minutes or until done.
Heat chicken in microwave after removing potato.
Stir chicken into potato.
Add salt and pepper (optional).
Add cheese (if desired).

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix zucchini, cheese, onion and dry ingredients.
Add egg and mix well.
Drop by heaping tablespoon into hot oil or bacon grease in skillet.
Brown then turn and brown other side.
Freezes well.

title: spam dish
directions: Mix together and place in 9 X 12 dish.
Pour one quart milk over all.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.
Serve with garlic bread.
Can be made ahead.
Freezes well.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Dip slices of toast in pan of warm water.
Squeeze out.
Saute pork sausage until no longer pink; add to bread.
Melt margarine in skillet; saute onion and celery just a little.
Add to bread mixture.
Add beaten eggs, salt and sage.
Add enough chicken broth to make as moist as you like.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, butter, egg and cinnamon. Add milk slowly, stirring constantly, then bread, raisins and vanilla. Place bowl of ingredients in pan of warm water and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Combine all ingredients. Form a ball. Roll in chopped nuts. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine cooked, cubed chicken with soup.
Add salt, onion, lemon juice, pimento and celery.
Add salad dressing (Miracle Whip or mayonnaise).
Put mixture into casserole dish.
Top with cheese, almonds and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes just before using to prevent discoloration. Combine ingredients in electric mixer bowl.
Beat on low speed until blended, scraping bowl.
Preheat frypan; grease lightly with butter or drippings.
Drop mixture by the spoonfuls, spreading out.
Bake until brown; turn and brown other side and bake until potatoes are done.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs together.
Sift all dry ingredients together and combine with creamed mixture well.
Add apples and nuts.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan and add mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: easy party meatballs
directions: Let the meatballs simmer all day, stirring occasionally. Leftovers can be used for meatball sandwiches.
The sauce is very tasty.

title: banana cream cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and mashed bananas thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour, salt, soda and buttermilk and mix well. Then add vanilla.

title: fat-free breakfast
directions: Put water and salt in a small frypan.
Bring to boil and add egg whites.
Poach until firm.
Heat asparagus.
Put egg whites on the unbuttered toast.
Cover with the asparagus or tomato slices. Season and enjoy!

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry pork chops medium done.
Place 3 pork chops in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup rice and 1/2 package of onion soup mix over them.
Place the other 3 pork chops on top of these.
Add remaining rice and soup mix.
Cover with water and bake at 350° until done.

title: creamy chicken and broccoli
directions: Prepare
stuffing
mix according to package directions; stir in 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spread stuffing mix over bottom of
greased
9-inch
round or square shallow casserole dish. Arrange broccoli spears with flowerets around the outer edge of dish.
Melt
cheese.
Add
milk
and
sour
cream
to cheese;
mix well.
Combine
chicken
and
cheese sauce;
mix well.
Pour mixture over broccoli stalks.
Bake, covered, for 30
minutes
Sprinkle remaining onions over chicken and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan and lightly dust the inside with flour.
Cream together the butter and 2 cups of the sugar.
Add eggs, blending well, then the sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture and beat until just blended.
Do not overbeat.

title: spiced punch
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Simmer over low heat 30 minutes.
Remove cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot. Makes 24 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, cheese, 1/2 cup cereal, soup, celery, onion, milk and pepper; mix well.
Spread into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine remaining cereal and butter; mix well. Sprinkle evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) about 20 minutes.

title: plain cake
directions: Measure the shortening in a bowl.
Sift in the flour and sugar.
Stir in the eggs and 1/4 cup of milk.
Beat 2 minutes or 300 strokes.
Add 3/4 cup milk and vanilla.
Beat 75 strokes.
Put mixture in a prepared cake pan and bake at 375° until done.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Slice vegetables into a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Mix other ingredients and pour over.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: hot chocolate(dry mix)
directions: Mix all together and use 1/3 cup of mix with 1 cup of hot water.

title: cherry whip
directions: Drain pineapple juice off.
Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Put in refrigerator and let chill.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into pie crust.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: lime buttermilk salad
directions: Mix jello with crushed pineapple.
Add buttermilk.
Stir in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.
Heat pineapple before stirring in jello.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make roux (brown over slow fire, stirring constantly) of flour and oil.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic; cook until soft.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste; mix well and cook about 5 minutes.
Add 6 cups water and let simmer about 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and set aside to cool. Mix cream cheese with a small amount of pineapple juice. When well mixed, add pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts to Jell-O and chill until firm.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients in small amount of cooking oil. Stir occasionally to separate.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 2 1/2 hours on stove top.
Stir frequently.
If sauce becomes too dry, add a small amount of water.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Spread bean dip in shallow dish.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning mix in bowl.
Mix well.
Spread over bean dip.
Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper in bowl. Spread over sour cream layer.
Sprinkle with tomatoes and green onions.
Top with cheese.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: corn bisque with clams
directions: Cook bacon.
Add flour to drippings in pot; stir over medium heat until mixture bubbles.
Slowly whisk in half and half. Stirring constantly, bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to blend.
Simmer, do not boil, for 1 to 2 minutes, until flavors have blended.
Ladle into mugs. Sprinkle bacon on top.
Makes 12 cups.

title: broadway brownie bars
directions: In small mixing bowl, blend 6 ounces cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons of flour, 1/4 cup butter, 1 egg and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Set aside.

title: rotel dip
directions: Put Ro-Tel in blender.
Melt cheese over double boiler.
Mix well.

title: zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in saucepan and cook, covered, 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Just before serving, sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and soy sauce.
Serve when cheese has thoroughly melted.
Serves 4 to 6.
This dish may look funny, but tastes great!

title: chicken sorento
directions: Flour chicken and lightly brown on both sides.
Place in baking dish and top with cheese, spinach and tomatoes; seasoning accordingly.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: cherries on snow christmas dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Press into bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Line sides with waxed paper. Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat milk; stir in gelatin and heat until gelatin melts.
Set aside.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Melt chocolate chips and wax together in top of double boiler. Combine remaining ingredients and form into small balls. Dip balls into melted chocolate. Place on waxed paper to dry. If desired, sprinkle with colored sugar.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pat into jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with the rest of ingredients.
Return to oven for another 20 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: super chili
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, warm the oil.
Add the onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until very tender, about 20 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cherry cake pudding
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, mix pie filling and water together; sprinkle cake mix on top of cherry filling.
Add pats of margarine on top of cake mix.
Bake 35 minutes or until golden brown in heated oven at 350°.

title: pineapple-cheese dish
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save 3 tablespoons of the juice.
Combine sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Add cheese, nuts and pineapple chunks; stir well.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine margarine and cracker crumbs; sprinkle over pineapple mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday spinach
directions: Combine sour cream and Hidden Valley mix.
Stir in artichokes, spinach and pimentos.
Cut slice off top of whole loaf of bread and hollow out center leaving 1-inch shell.
Reserve the bread for dipping.
Also use cubed bread for dipping.
Serve warm or cold. To serve warm, bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen beans in salted water; drain (if using canned beans, omit salt).
Combine milk, soup and pepper; pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can onions. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with 1/2 can onions and pimiento; bake 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured well.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Cool; top with chocolate icing.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Beat eggs and oil. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a Pam sprayed 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: no-bake dessert cake
directions: In a large bowl, tear up cake.
Mix in Cool Whip and prepared pudding to coat cake.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch cake pan and smooth. Top with cherries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix the sugar, corn syrup, salt and peanuts thoroughly in a glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes; stir.
Microwave 3 1/2 more minutes, then stir in butter.
Cook 2 more minutes. Add vanilla and soda; stir.
Pour out immediately onto greased pan.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: vegetable salad vinaigrette
directions: Drain corn and peas.
Add onions and pimento.
In saucepan, combine oil, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil and pour over salad.
Refrigerate overnight.
You may drain before serving if you want to.
However, the dressing acts as a preservative if left over and it will keep for a long while in the refrigerator.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg white until real fluffy, about 10 minutes.
Fold in other ingredients.
Pour into prepared pie shell and freeze.

title: lemon bundt cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and beat 8 to 10 minutes. Bake in Bundt pan at 375° for 45 minutes. Remove from pan immediately and pour over a glaze of the last 3 ingredients.

title: low-fat marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine frozen vegetables and chickpeas in a bowl.
In a jar with a tight fitting lid, shake the salad dressing, juice, concentrate, oil, vinegar, lemon juice, garlic and pepper to mix well.
Pour over vegetable-bean mixture.
Mix well.
Let marinate a few hours in refrigerator.
Arrange salad over lettuce leaves. Serve chilled.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving all juice.
Add juice to jello in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water.
Heat to boiling, stirring to dissolve jello.
Remove from heat.
Blend in cranberry sauce. Add lemon juice, peel and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Blend sour cream into jello mixture.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Pour into a greased 2-quart mold.
Chill firm.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Slice onion and squash. Boil and drain. Lightly beat eggs and combine with rest of ingredients. Pour into a buttered casserole dish and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 425 degrees for 1 hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt 1 1/2 cups butter; add 1 cup sugar and add mixture to crushed pretzels.
Pat into 9 x 3-inch pan.
Mix Dream Whip, cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar and pour over pretzel mixture.
Drain pineapple.
Put juice in the saucepan and add cornstarch.
Blend; cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Fold in crushed pineapple and when cool, add to the top of the cream cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: crunchy frozen punch(50 cups)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, then combine sugar and 4 cups water and bring to boil.
Add to jello mixture and set aside to cool.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Place beef in large pan.
Cover with beer, catsup and onion soup mix.
Bake, covered, 3 hours at 350° or all day in a crock-pot.
Separate with fork.
It will absorb all liquid.

title: refreshing iced tea punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags and steep for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and lemonade; chill.
Before serving, add ginger ale. Serves 8 to 10.

title: swiss medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 cup onions. Pour into greased casserole. Bake covered 30 minutes at 350°. Top with cheese and onion. Bake uncovered 5 more minutes.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar and butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until butter is melted (6 to 8 minutes).
In large mixer bowl, combine cooked mixture with ice cream.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often.
Beat until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
Store refrigerated up to 2 weeks or frozen up to 1 month.

title: pecan pumpkin cake
directions: Combine cake mix,
pecans
and
spices in bowl.
Mix in eggs, pumpkin and 1/3
less
water
than is called for in cake mix directions.
Add
raisins.
Bake
in a greased tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Glaze or frost.

title: barbecue sauce(for steak or wild game)
directions: Except meat, combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Place 3 pounds meat in pan in oven or low setting in crock-pot, covering with liquid as you normally would but include the barbecue sauce.
Bake 2 hours in a 350° oven.
Crock-pot time as you normally would.
When the water is poured from crock-pot, meat is left losing that gamey taste and with a treat of barbecue flavor.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well with electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: tangy tuna spread(low-fat)
directions: Add vegetables to tuna.
Combine yogurt, honey, lemon juice and mustard.
Mix fish and vegetables until evenly distributed. Spread on toast or crackers and serve.

title: raspberry nut cookies(rich's cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add salt, vanilla and egg yolk; beat. Add flour and stir until blended.
Divide dough in 3 parts, on floured board.
Shape dough in rolls 1-inch thick.
Cut rolls in 3/4-inch pieces; shape into balls.
Dip balls in slightly beaten egg white, then roll in almonds.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Make indentation in top of each.
Fill with 1/4 teaspoon jam.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli.
Layer broccoli, then chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry together.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Add sugar to juice.
Add flour to beaten eggs.	Mix all together and boil until
creamy.
Cool
and add whipped cream. Makes a lot.

title: curling club frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
It's easy and delicious.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Mix
shortening,
brown sugar, molasses and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Add buttermilk.
Mix spices in flour.
Add soda and salt to	flour.	Add
flour
mixture by hand.
Stir until smooth. Spread
thin
in
cake pans (8 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch) and bake at 350°.
This should make 5 or 6 thin layers.

title: polish baked beans
directions: Place beans in a slow cooker with sauerkraut, sausage and brown sugar.
Stir well and cook in slow cooker approximately 3 hours.

title: apple nut squares
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Set aside.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in egg mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt together.
Add 3 eggs and mix well.
Add 3 more eggs and mix well.
Pour in milk and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 9-inch deep dish pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350° and cook for 30 minutes longer.

title: broccoli with shrimp sauce
directions: In a saucepan, blend the chive cream cheese and milk over low heat.
Add cream of shrimp soup and stir until hot.
Pour over drained broccoli and sprinkle toasted, slivered almonds on top. Also good with cauliflower.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: taco pie
directions: Simmer first three ingredients 10 minutes.
Line bottom and sides of greased pie tin with crescent rolls.
Place all remaining ingredients in layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage casserole(serves 6)
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion in 1/2 stick margarine until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is slightly thickened.
Line a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with sausage.
Add 1/2 the potatoes, 1/2 the peas and 1/2 the sauce. Repeat layers.
Combine 1/2 stick melted butter and bread crumbs. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Add sugar to well beaten eggs, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder.
Lastly, add margarine or butter melted in hot milk.
Bake at 350° in an 8-inch cake pan.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Blend cheese, pimento, mayo, soup and onion with cooked macaroni.
Pour into baking dish.
Crush crackers and spread over macaroni mixture.
Melt 3 to 4 tablespoons butter or margarine and pour over topping.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cook cake as directed.
Heat, but do not boil milk and sugar. Pour over cake; fork cake.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip, then strawberries or coconut.

title: ham, swiss and mushroom pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Make pizza dough according to directions.
Place in center of pan and press out.
Bake for 5 to 10 minutes until a light golden brown. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, horseradish, mustard and poppy seed.
Blend well.
Spread over partially baked crust.
Top with green peppers, onions, ham and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with cheeses. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until crust is a golden brown and cheese is melted.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Butter an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Lay 3 raw noodles in pan. Pour 1/3 jar of sauce.
Mix cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, spinach and Mozzarella cheese. Pour 1/3 of this over sauce. Repeat layers ending with noodles.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: apple walnut cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 cup walnuts.
Place apples in bottom of greased 8-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and butter or oleo.
Add dry ingredients all at once and beat until smooth.
Pour batter over apples.
Sprinkle with remaining walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: french onion soup
directions: *Brush 1 piece of French bread with melted butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and basil.
Toast in 350° oven for 15 minutes until crisp and lightly brown.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Stir milk, pineapple, lemon juice, and whipped topping.
Pour into piecrust.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: italian cookie biscotti
directions: Combine sugar and butter; add milk to make soft.
Should be runny.
Dip cookie into icing.

title: microwave lutefish
directions: Put milk in a saucepan over medium burner.
Mix cornstarch in a little cold milk.
Add this to hot milk, stirring the whole time.
Add butter, salt and pepper after it comes to a boil and is getting thick.
Pour Cream Sauce over fish and boiled potatoes.

title: potato chip ham casserole
directions: Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Cook until smooth. Add ham and pour into greased casserole.
Top with thick layer of potato chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place frozen broccoli in casserole, side by side.
Mix mayonnaise, mushroom soup and egg together and pour over broccoli.
After about 35 minutes, take from oven and spread cheese over it.
Top with chips or bread crumbs or both and bake 1/2 hour or until cheese is melted and top is lightly browned.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly; rub skins with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, or until done.
Allow potatoes to cool to touch.
Cut in half lengthwise; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving 1/8 to 1/4-inch shells.
(Pulp may be used for mashed potatoes or served for another recipe.)
Cut shells in half crosswise; deep fry in hot oil (375°) for 2 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Place skins on a baking sheet; sprinkle with salt, cheese and bacon.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream.
Yields 1 dozen appetizer servings.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients, except for ice cubes, into blender. Blend well adding one ice cube at a time.
Serve immediately.
Can add orange slice for garnish.

title: jicama salad with citrus dressing
directions: Cut jicama into thick julienne strips.
Combine jicama and red onions in serving bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a covered jar; shake to mix.
Pour dressing over jicama and toss.
Serving size:
1/8 recipe.
Calories:
Protein:
1 g. Carbohydrates: 8 g. Total Fat:
1 g. Saturated:
Trace.
Cholesterol:
0 mg. Fiber:
less than 1 g. Sodium:
5 mg.
Diabetic Exchange:
2 vegetables.

title: placki z kartofli (potato pancakes)
directions: Pour off dark water accumulated on top of grated potatoes. Add the other ingredients and beat well.
With spoon, drop mixture on hot griddle and spread as thinly as possible.
Fry on both sides.
To prevent potatoes from darkening, add 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
An old Polish cook saying, "A noisy cow gives little milk: Great talkers are little doers."

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix with sugar and flour.
Pour 3 tablespoons juice over mixture and mix.
Add cheese.
Spray dish with Pam, then add ingredients.
Melt butter and add to crackers. Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes.

title: polska kielbasa jambalaya
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
While rice is cooking, coat inside of large skillet with new butter-flavor Pam cooking spray according to directions; heat skillet over medium heat.
Add kielbasa, onion, green pepper and celery; saute until veggies are tender.
Add tomatoes, pepper sauce and pepper.
Drain rice and stir into kielbasa mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the butter and cheese.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add cake mix (dry), 1/3 at a time, mixing well after each addition. If mixer is used, add last third of cake mix by hand.
Cover. Chill 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop by scant teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.

title: hugs and chips cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With a mixer, beat cream cheese until it is fluffy; gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth. Add egg and vanilla; mix well.

title: mama eula's coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two layers.
Bake; when completely cool, split both layers.

title: pierogi
directions: Cook potato and drain.
Mash and cool.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken and place in a baking dish.
Add salt, pepper and margarine.
Place in oven and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until tender.
Drain off drippings.
Add mushroom soup and cooking wine.
Bake 1/2 hour longer.
Cut in pieces.
Delicious with mashed potatoes and green beans.

title: dirty rice
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Pour in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Combine all ingredients in separate bowl.
Pour Jell-O over ingredients and mix together.
Pour into mold and let set.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
Fill center with cottage cheese.

title: cake mix drop cookies
directions: Mix cake mix with nuts and shortening.
Blend thoroughly with electric mixer.
Add egg and water; mix thoroughly.
Dough will be quite stiff.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool on wire rack.

title: spinach-sausage quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 375°.
In medium skillet, cook sausage, green onion and garlic over medium heat until sausage is done, stirring occasionally.
Drain sausage fat and stir in spinach and stuffing mix.
Sprinkle first cheese and then sausage mixture in pie shell. In medium bowl, combine egg and half and half with fork.
Pour egg mixture over sausage in pastry shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.

title: peanut butter cereal candy
directions: Mix cereal and peanuts; set aside.
Combine sugar and syrup in heavy pot; cook on medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Immediately pour syrup over cereal mixture, stirring gently to coat.
Pat evenly into buttered pan. Cool.
Cut into 2-inch bars.

title: cheese and sausage bake
directions: Use a 9 x 11-inch baking dish, greased.
Cover bottom of pan with white bread.
Fry sausage, drain well and spread over bread layer.
Mix eggs and milk; spread over sausage layer.
Spread Cheddar cheese over egg mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 or 45 minutes.
Ham may be used in place of sausage.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown rice and onion in butter.
Mix beef broth and 1 can of water.
Bake for 1 hour or until juice is cooked out.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken linguine
directions: Drain and saute mushrooms in wine over high heat for 5 minutes.
In a saucepan, cover chicken with water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes
Drain, cool and shred.
Add onion to saucepan with 1 tablespoon water.
Saute.
Add flour and 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Add 2 1/2 cups chicken broth and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Combine mushroom mixture, chicken and sour cream mixture with cooked linguine, Monterey Jack cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan and pepper.
Spoon into a 13 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray. Combine bread crumbs and remaining Parmesan cheese with margarine. Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute broccoli and onions in butter.
Add flour and stir. Pour in stock and add seasonings.
Cook 30 minutes until broccoli is soft.
Take off heat and take out bay leaf.
Puree broccoli mixture.
Mix egg yolks and cream together.
Stir into broccoli mixture; heat thoroughly.
Pour into bowls and garnish with parsley.

title: chess pie bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and put in ungreased 9 x 13 pan.

title: chocolate chip applesauce cake
directions: Mix oil and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beat in eggs. Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cocoa.
Add applesauce and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle top of batter with 2 tablespoons sugar, nuts and chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can divide recipe in half and bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: deep fried onion rings
directions: Mix well; should look like melted ice cream.
Slice onion as desired.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Fix cake mix according to instruction. Punch holes in hot cake; pour milk and butterscotch sauce over cake. Place in refrigerator over night. Spread cool whip on top, then sprinkle with crushed heath bars.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Add enough water to make 2 cups. Bring to a boil.
Dissolve jello and cream cheese in this liquid. Add the Coca-Cola, fruit and nuts.
Chill until set.
Makes 12 servings.

title: lo-fat pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together sugar and applesauce; add eggs, water, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat in pumpkin.
Makes 2 regular loaves or can make muffins.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour mixture in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chili for two
directions: Cook ground beef, green pepper, onion and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, undrained kidney beans, undrained tomatoes, chili powder, salt, basil and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes. Serve over hot rice if desired.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Place diced vegetables in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add hamburger and remaining ingredients. Mix well. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Uncover.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles and bake another 30 minutes.

title: sausage and pancake breakfast
directions: Combine pancake mix, milk, eggs and oil.
Beat until nearly smooth.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Crosswise, arrange sausages over batter in pattern to be cut into 12 squares.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with your favorite syrup.

title: danish cucumber salad
directions: Thinly slice cucumbers.
Mix with 2 teaspoons salt.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and cream together.
Cook chicken and pick meat off bones and lay chicken pieces in bottom of baking dish.
Pour the soups and cream over chicken.
Mix dressing with chicken broth according to package directions and add butter.
Place on top of chicken and soups.
Bake about 35 minutes on 425° or until brown.

title: new mexico cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased shallow pan (9-inch square or larger).
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for about 45 minutes or until firm.
Yield: 1 large loaf.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Put in casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup crushed Ritz crackers. Melt 1 stick oleo and pour over crackers.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: the "best" potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool and slice (4 cups).
Mix mayonnaise, cottage cheese and chives with seasonings.
Layer potatoes, onions and mayonnaise mixture again and again.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Toss before serving.
Be sure to cover well before refrigerating.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions. Cool. Prepare pudding according to package directions in a punch bowl. Crumble 1/3 of cake layer and 1/3 of the remaining ingredients in the following order: coconut, cherry pie filling, Cool Whip and pecans. Repeat this 2 more times, ending in Cool Whip. Sprinkle with pecans and cherries. Chill and serve.

title: hungarian spaghetti (zutone)
directions: Saute peppers and onion in margarine.
Add soup and sauce. Stir well.
Brown meat and add liquid from mushrooms and garlic. Cook spaghetti as per directions on the box.
Mix all ingredients together, except 1 1/2 cups of the cheese.
Put in a greased roasting pan.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: coconut toasted muffins
directions: Mix butter, coconut, brown sugar and mace.
Spread on muffins and broil until golden brown.

title: peach punch
directions: Mix together and serve.
Yields 100 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add to powdered sugar, vanilla, graham crackers and peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Roll with hands into small balls.
Lay out on wax paper and set aside.

title: lime delite
directions: Follow directions for jello.
Add marshmallows.
Set aside to cool.
Mash cream cheese and add to mayonnaise.
Add to cooled jello mixture.
Add pineapple and juice.
Add pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms. Beat for 30 seconds. Drop dough by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake about 10 minutes at 450° or until lightly brown. Mix margarine, garlic powder and parsley flakes. Brush over warm Bisquick before removing from cookie sheet. Serve warm. Makes about 12 biscuits.

title: diane's "seafood" appetizer
directions: Combine sea legs, mayo and spices.
