Split bread lengthwise. Coat each half with cheese spread.
Top with sea leg mixture and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: 125 year old black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla and walnut flavoring. Mix milk slowly until thoroughly mixed.
Fold in black walnuts. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased 3-quart casserole.
Cover with corn flakes and pour 1/2 stick of oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in flour, soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Combine with Rice Krispies and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: beef curry
directions: Cut meat into bite-size cubes and dredge through flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Add onion and garlic and saute until brown.
Add to crock-pot with remaining ingredients.
Cook on low while you are at work.
Serve over rice with diced hard-boiled eggs, diced cucumber, crumbled bacon, raisins, diced apples and chopped onion.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Mix well.
Dip out on waxed paper.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter; spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Pour butter over top and bake at 400° about 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple praline pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seder charoses(apples)
directions: Chop apples and nuts fine and mix together with wine.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box and add peanut butter and sugar. Mix well. Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: cake cookie bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and butter.
(Reserve 1 cup of this for the topping.)
Beat egg, salt, vanilla, baking soda and milk.
Add brown sugar mixture that is left in the bowl and mix well.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: different lemon icebox pie
directions: Add lemon juice to milk.
Fold in whipped cream. Pour in a graham cracker crust, vanilla wafer crust or pastry crust and chill.
Can be topped with more whipped cream, strawberries or shaved chocolate.

title: low-fat squash casserole
directions: Mix well, except for crackers.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over top.
Bake at 350° until firm in the center.
May substitute broccoli for squash.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together, one-half cup at a time. Add the eggs, one at a time.
Combine the flour and salt and add a small amount at a time.
Lastly, add the buttermilk.
The batter should look like a cake mix that needs more flour.
Cook in an unbaked pie shell at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until the pie is golden brown.

title: crescent roll casserole
directions: Brown the meat and onion together, then add frozen peas and Cheddar cheese soup.
Mix and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Grate block cheese.
Using 2 cans crescent dinner rolls, lay 2 rectangle shapes together.
Fill with cheese and roll up.
Slice about 3/4 to 1-inch thick and lay on top of casserole.
Spread rest of cheese on top.
Cook as directed for the rolls.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Skin, slice and cook carrots.
Slice onion and leave in rings; cut green pepper into thin strips.
In a bowl have ready and mix together oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, tomato soup, sugar, onion and pepper.
Put drained carrots into sauce and cover tightly; refrigerate.
Will keep for 3 weeks.

title: microwavable rice stuffed peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from end of peppers; remove seeds and membrane. Rinse.
Arrange peppers in a 9-inch pie plate.
Mix remaining ingredients except water.
Fill each pepper with 2/3 cup mixture. Spoon 2 tablespoons water into each pepper.
Cover loosely and microwave 6 minutes.
Rotate plate 1/2 turn and microwave 4 to 5 minutes longer.

title: mock sausage
directions: Mash beans. Add sage, salt, pepper and butter.
Mix well. Form patties. Roll in crumbs, dip in eggs, roll in crumbs and fry until brown.

title: haystack candy
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips in microwave.
Add noodles and nuts.
Stir until well coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Can be put in refrigerator to set.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add pumpkin mixture alternately with orange juice.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour batter into pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas scents
directions: Combine all ingredients in a tea kettle or saucepan and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer as long as desired.
Check often and add additional water if needed.
May store in refrigerator for several days and be reused.
Ideal to set on wood heating stoves!

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Mix other ingredients and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.

title: mousse brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350 F, grease bottom only of 9 x 13 pan.
Prepare brownie mix as directed on package.
Spread in pan.
Heat whipping cream and chocolate chips in 2 qt sauce pan, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth; cook slightly. Beat eggs, sugar and salt until eggs are foamy.
Stir into chocolate mixture.
Pour evenly over batter in pan.
Bake 45 minutes, cool 2 hrs, cut into 2-inch squares.
Keep refrigerated.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Spread pecans and coconut in pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix sugar, margarine and cream cheese. Spread over cake layer and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dilled yellow squash casserole
directions: In a 2-quart square baking dish, combine squash, onion, butter, 1/2 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes, or until squash is just tender; stirring once.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix first five ingredients in blender or mixer.
Then add parsley.
If you like French dressing, this is a delicious dressing.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add zucchini sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture.
Fold in nuts. Spoon batter into 2 loaf pans, sprayed with Pam or grease and flour.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: This is enough for 2 pounds of ground beef, approximately 1/2 cup.
To prepare mix, use a plastic zip-type bag, combine all ingredients and shake the bag until completely mixed.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together, adding nuts last.
Pour into an	unbaked
pie crust.
Then place in 350° oven, cooking until you think it is completely cooked.

title: cranberry-banana nut bread
directions: Combine berries, 1 cup sugar and water in medium saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat and cook until berries pop. Drain and set aside.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Brown cube steak with onion.
Place browned cube steak in casserole dish.
Mix soup with equal amount of milk.
Pour over cube steak.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: festive punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid using about 1/2 amount of water called for.
Mix all other juices.
Add soda when ready to serve.

title: potato puffs
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
mixing
well.
Shape
into balls. Roll
in beaten eggs, then in crushed cornflakes.
You may
want to add salt to this recipe or to use more cheese to taste.
Heat the puffs in a 325° oven until hot.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Cook vegetables in unsalted water following package directions; drain. Stir in onion. Combine remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour over mixed vegetables. Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving. Stir vegetables occasionally. Serve as a relish or a salad.
Serves 6.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Chill and serve with chips or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pizza
directions: First add beard.
Add sos.
Add unens and cheasse abb pearonts.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
In covered saucepan, cook soup mix, rice and water; add chopped vegetables.
Combine mixture with sausage.
Put into a 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Layer top with thin slices of Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: crackling bacon corn cakes
directions: In a skillet cook bacon and onion over medium heat until bacon is brown.
Meanwhile combine flour, chives, baking powder, salt and cayenne pepper.
Stir in milk, egg and oil until moistened.
Stir in bacon and onion and remaining ingredients, except maple syrup. Heat griddle to 350°.
Pour about one-third cup batter on greased griddle, cook until corn cakes are golden brown; 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Serve with warm maple syrup.

title: soft corn shells
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Have a large skillet and spray with no stick spray.
Heat on medium heat, then pour 1/3 cup of batter into hot skillet.
Brown on both sides and put your filling in and enjoy.

title: chewy chocolate bars
directions: *Or if you omit coconut, put in 1 cup chopped nuts instead.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st layer:
(Bottom) 1 block butter mixed with 2 cups crushed cookies.

title: pudding peanut clusters
directions: Mix ingredients, except nuts.
Cook and stir to a full boil. Lower heat and continue stirring while mixture boils slowly for three minutes.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Drop from teaspoon onto buttered wax paper or foil.

title: oatmeal apple raisin muffins(sugar-free)
directions: Beat egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400°
for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potatoes deluxe(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Thaw hash browns in package for 30 minutes.
Combine all the ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased glass pan.
Top with crushed potato chips or corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: e-z fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Add about 1 1/2 cups of mixed fruit juices back to fruit.
Sprinkle dry instant pudding over fruit and mix gently. Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Stir before serving.

title: crawfish cornbread dressing
directions: Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions.
Bake. Mix all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour mixture into crumbled cornbread.
Spread, after mixing, into pan and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
(Add more seasoning if desired.) Yields enough for 20 to 30 people.

title: sugar cookies
directions: For shortening, I use butter flavor Crisco.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg; beat until fluffy.
Stir in milk. Sift together dry ingredients; blend well.
Chill 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour and other dry ingredients.
Mix oil and sugar; add dry ingredients.
Mix well; add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Add vanilla, rest of the flour and eggs, one at a time.
Blend well. Bake at 350° in 2 or 3 cake pans.
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting (recipe follows).

title: ice cream pie
directions: Place ice cream in bowl and stir until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Blend well.
Spoon
into crust.
Freeze until firm, at least 4 hours.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Note:
This is not the Ritz cracker pie.

title: eggplant-chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with garlic powder, salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cookie dough
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with an electric mixer.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour one cup at a time, mixing after each addition. The dough will be very stiff; blend last of the flour by hand. Do not chill dough.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar, cocoa, eggs, flour, pecans and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
When done, spread with Marshmallow Creme and let cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco and sugars until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Add flour slowly and stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by heaping tablespoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 14 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix cake according to directions, substituting water with reserved juice, add water if needed.
Bake in 2 layers according to directions.
Mix cool whip with strawberries, frost cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain one can of green beans, keep liquid of the other.
Mix this with mushroom soup.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add onion rings and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: pimento-cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator for 45 minutes. Then make into sandwiches or cut into desired shapes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour gradually while beating the mixture.
Add chopped nuts, then vanilla.
Shape into a loaf.
Let stand in icebox until it can be sliced (couple of hours).
Slice and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: "eat the pan" meat loaf
directions: Cut the zucchini in half lengthwise and scoop out the center. Prepare your meat loaf recipe as usual.
Mound the meat loaf in the zucchini halves.
Bake according to meat loaf recipe.
Remove from oven and serve.
There's no clean-up because you can eat the "pan."

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Pour cheese over pineapple.
In pan, mix sugar, juice of pineapple and flour. Bring to boil to medium thick.
Pour over cheese and top with buttered breadcrumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ginny's spaghetti sauce(for 25)
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Cook meat until tender.
Grind vegetables and cook in oil until soft.
Add 3 cups water, tomato paste and tomato juice.
Mix all together and simmer for 3 hours. This will feed 25 people, or you may freeze in small containers for your family use.

title: 7 layer bean dip
directions: Combine beans and taco seasoning. Mix well.
Cover bottom of 8-inch dish.
Layer sour cream, guacamole, cheese, salsa, chiles and green onions. Serve with chips.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Rinse the chicken wings and pat them dry.
Cut off and discard wing tips.
Cut each wing at the joint to make 2 sections.
Arrange the chicken pieces in one layer in an ungreased baking pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Drain fat from pan.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together, pour into pan and bake at 375°.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Layer onto a large plate or 9 x 13-inch pan:

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 6 x 10-inch dish. Bake until light brown (25 minutes).

title: caramel apples
directions: Wash and dry apples; remove stems.
Insert a wooden skewer into the stem end of each apple.
In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and dash of salt; mix well.
Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly. Stir in condensed milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, to 245° (firm-ball stage) for 12 to 15 minutes (mixture should boil gently over entire surface).
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Dip each apple into caramel mixture; turn to coat.
Set on a buttered baking sheet; chill.
Makes 14 coated apples.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Place partly thawed broccoli in buttered baking dish; combine other ingredients, except cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
About the last 15 minutes of baking time, dot with cheese.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar, water and coffee in a saucepan and simmer 1 hour. Let cool.
Add vanilla and vodka to cooled mixture.
Bottle it.

title: chocolate mint brownies
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: scalloped cheese potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes and soup.

Layer half of the mixture in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Dot with half of the butter and sprinkle with half of the cheese. Repeat layers. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until the potatoes are tender.
Yields 12 servings.

title: citrus marshmallow dessert
directions: Cut marshmallows in quarters; put into double boiler; add orange juice and cook until marshmallows are thoroughly dissolved. Chill slightly; pour into sherbert glasses; chill in refrigerator and serve with whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: perfect potato salad
directions: Sprinkle cooked potatoes with sugar and vinegar. Add onion, celery, seasoning and mayonnaise. Toss to blend.
Carefully fold in egg slices. Chill. Trim with egg slices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: soft dutch pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 1/2 cups of warm water.
Add sugar and salt.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Turn dough out onto floured surface and knead until smooth (5 minutes).
Roll into circle and divide into 8 pieces.
Roll each piece until 12 to 15 inches long, thin as a pencil and shape into pretzel.
Place foil on cookie sheet (shiny side up).
Beat 1 egg yolk and 1 tablespoon water and baste onto pretzels.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 8 pretzels.

title: fingerprint cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and flour.
Roll in balls.
Press thumbprint; fill with jelly.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions.
Combine milk and meat.
Divide into 5 patties.
On waxed paper, pat each patty into a 6-inch circle.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each patty. Draw meat over stuffing and seal very well.
Place in crock-pot. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Do not stir. Cook in covered crock-pot for 8 hours on low heat.
Pour gravy over each patty before serving.

title: avocado salad - el patio
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle with garlic and salt to taste.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter and the sugars until smooth. Add beaten eggs.
Mix with salt, flour and soda.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 minutes.

title: kraut
directions: Fill quart jars with chopped cabbage.
Put 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon sugar to 1 quart of cabbage.
Fill with boiling water. Seal.

title: souper meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup mushroom soup, onion soup mix, beef, crumbs and egg.
In 2-quart, oblong baking dish, firmly shape into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done. Spoon off fat.
Reserve 1 to 2 tablespoons of drippings.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Blend sugar and shortening; stir in eggs.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, cream of tartar and salt.
Add to shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Decorate with colored sprinkles, etc., after flattening with bottom of glass.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: good roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place roast in roasting pan with cover. Sprinkle onion soup mix all over the roast.
In bowl, mix mushroom soup, 1 can water, chopped onion and jar of mushrooms; stir until well combined.
Pour over roast.
Cover; place in oven for 1 hour. After 1 hour, remove from oven and turn roast over, then place potatoes all around.
Cover and return to oven 1 more hour.
Remove and serve with carrots, corn or my favorite green beans.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: english tea scones
directions: Heat the oven to 400°.
Mix the flour and butter with your hands.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Mix with your hands again. Add the milk and mix again.
Roll the dough until it is 1/2-inch thick.
Cut the dough into 1 1/2-inch sections.
Bake the sections on a greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Delicious served with tea or wassail.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, powdered sugar, butter, shortening and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll in balls, flatten with glass, dipped in sugar on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 or 10 minutes.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Before cooking, pour lemon juice over lamb (this will get rid of wild taste).
Insert 3 or 4 whole cloves of garlic into lamb. The garlic will give the lamb a really good taste.
Place leg of lamb in baking dish, pour at least 1-inch of water into dish and cook in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 4 more hours.

title: plain pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt together and cut in shortening with 2 knives or pastry blender.
Add water, using only a small portion at a time, until mixture wil hold together.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll out on floured board to desired size.

Line the pie pan with one piece of dough, being careful not to stretch dough. After filling is placed in pastry, dampen edges of lower crust with cold water and cover with remaining dough which has been slashed in several places to allow steam to escape while baking. Press edges together with prongs of fork and bake according to recipe for filling selected.
Makes 2 (9-inch) shells or one 2-crust (9-inch) pie.

title: pickled squash
directions: Put squash and onions together and salt; set aside 1 hour. Drain well.
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and pepper; bring to a good boil.
Add squash and onions; let it come to a boil.
Put in pint jars and seal.

title: harvest casserole
directions: In 8-quart pot brown eggplant in oil, stir.
Drain on paper towels.
Brown next 3 veggies, stir.
Add water, boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until tender.
Remove from heat, stir in eggplant, beans, tomato sauce, paste, salt, basil and pepper. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes in 2 (12 x 8-inch) dishes or one large dish.
Add cheese 5 minutes before removing from oven.

title: special shrimp pasta salad
directions: Combine all of the spices with the liquid Butter Buds, fat-free mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Combine shrimp, pasta, green peppers, onion and celery.
Mix dressing with vegetables, pasta and shrimp.
Cover and chill overnight.
The longer it sets, the better the flavor.

title: cherry delights
directions: Mix margarine and sugar. Stir in corn syrup and the 2 egg yolks.
Stir in the flour; chill. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip into slightly beaten egg whites, then into 2 cups finely chopped nuts.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Press candied cherry halves into centers. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Note:
Chill the butter and shortening thoroughly in the freezer.

title: never fail pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine and mix with sugar, corn meal, water, vanilla and eggs.
Add chopped or whole pecans.
Pour into pie shells and bake 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lime salad
directions: Sprinkle jello on cottage cheese.
Add Mandarin oranges and pineapple (drain both well).
Mix well and fold in 1 container (2 cups) Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: easy broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil or steam broccoli for just a few minutes.
Blend the soup, milk and cheese.
Drain broccoli and arrange in an ungreased shallow 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix.
In a large bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Press mixture evenly into bottom and 3/4 up the sides of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: family-size banana pudding
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar and flour.
Beat yolks slightly.
Mix yolks with milk, adding just a little at a time to make a smooth mixture. Mix slowly with flour and sugar.
Cook in double boiler or heavy pot until it begins to thicken; cool a little.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; cool, peel and grate.
Heat butter with soup.
Blend in sour cream, onion and cheese.
Mix with potatoes and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Save broth. Cut up chicken in pieces and set aside.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Add to this chicken pieces.
Cook broccoli.
Heat soup.
Layer noodles, broccoli, cheese and soup.
Do not mix.
Top with French onions.
Microwave 30 minutes on Medium power or bake in 325° oven for one hour.

title: meal in a basket
directions: Stir-fry chicken in hot skillet; drain on paper towels.
Serve with deviled eggs and ham biscuits.

title: stew
directions: Make roux with equal amounts of oil and flour. Brown until it looks like a reddish color appears. Add onions and cook until tender, then add peppers, garlic, parsley flakes and onion tops and cook until golden.

title: squaw bread
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Add salt and sugar.
Stir in flour and baking powder

title: coconut crisp
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Spoon clusters on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together butter and crumbs.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat eggs until thick and light, about 5 minutes.
Add confectioners sugar, butter and vanilla.
Beat together another 5 minutes.
Spread over crumbs and chill for 30 minutes.
Spread with well drained pineapple.
Arrange banana slices over pineapple.
Spread whipped topping over bananas.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and decorate with cherries.
Sprinkle with coconut. Chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients, blend well and cover tightly to store in refrigerator.
Roll out required amount needed.
Cut and bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
It is not necessary to let rise.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: brownies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and 1 1/3 cups shortening.
Add flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt.
Mix well.
Add Karo syrup and vanilla.
Add nuts if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be baked in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch jelly roll pan.
Cream 1/2 cup shortening, 1/2 cup margarine and vanilla.
Add powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons of cocoa. Gradually add milk until desired spreading consistency.

title: butter ring cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, salt and almonds. Pack into cookie press and squeeze through the wreathed shaped design.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Do not grease the cookie sheet.

title: easy artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes until all liquid is removed.
Chop artichokes and add mayonnaise and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until "bubbly."
Serve hot with crackers.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Place slice of onion on top of each pork chop, then mix together brown sugar, salt and catsup.
Pour this over pork chops in covered casserole.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: oreo pudding
directions: Crush the cookies; put some in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix Cool Whip and ice cream together; put on top of crumbs.
Put the rest of crumbs on top and freeze.

title: nachos
directions: Arrange a layer of nacho chips on a microwavable platter. Spoon a small amount of salsa onto each chip.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Microwave at full power for 20 to 30 seconds to melt cheese.

title: pumpkin spice drops
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening with sugars.
Beat in eggs, pumpkin and vanilla.
Sift the flour, baking soda and spices into a bowl; pour any bran remaining in sifter.
Add the flour mixture to the pumpkin batter and stir in raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake in 375° oven 12 to 15 minutes. Cool and serve.
Each of the 36 cookies has 1 gram of fat and 37 calories.

title: autumn soup
directions: In large sauce pan cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Cook and stir onions and meat until onions are tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except tomatoes.
Heat until boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, cover and simmer 10 minutes longer or until vegetable are tender.

title: rich and creamy fudge
directions: In small saucepan, melt margarine and chocolate chips, stirring until smooth.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together the sweet potatoes, milk, eggs and sugar.
Then add vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread evenly with celery soup from can over chicken.
Spread Veg-All.
Spread mushroom and then chicken soup.

title: white potatoes and onion casserole
directions: Wash, peel and slice potatoes and onions and sprinkle the slices with salt and pepper.
Place potatoes and onion slices in alternate layers in a buttered baking dish; sprinkle with some paprika.
Mix the flour with the water and pour over the vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour batter into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Bring juice to boil. Pour over jello and dissolve.
Let cool; add 2 small Coca-Colas. Crumble cream cheese in small pieces.
Combine with nuts and add to other mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaves if desired.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Add these together.
Cook over medium heat until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes.
Then add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until thick.

title: no sugar added - oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, mix dry ingredients and set aside. In a large bowl, mix the butter and syrup, then beat in the egg and vanilla extract. Stir in the dry ingredients until mixture is well blended. Fold in chips. Add chips and nuts (if desired) and mix. Drop tablespoons of dough onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool on a wire rack.

title: creole seafood seasoning
directions: Put all ingredients in a food processor for about 1 minute. Use to season Creole sauce and other Cajun dishes.

title: my daughter's brownies
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, celery, onion, peas, eggs, bacon bits and mayonnaise.
Seal mayonnaise to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle lightly with garlic salt and top with grated cheese.
Cover in refrigerator for 6 to 12 hours before serving.

title: eggless raisin cake
directions: In large saucepan, boil raisins with water for 10 minutes, then add margarine and let cool.
Now in the same pan, put remaining ingredients.
Mix it.
You do not need to sift the ingredients. Bake in a greased 10 x 10-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. (You can add nuts but it is very good without.)

title: easy prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, spices and soda together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add prunes.
Mix well.
Drop in nuts; mix.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: maryland crab cakes(origin: usa)
directions: Combine egg, 3/4 cup bread crumbs, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Fold in crabmeat.
Blend.
Shape mixture into patties.
Coat patties with bread crumbs.
Refrigerate patties one hour.
Fry in shallow oil in frypan until browned.

title: unbaked cheese cake
directions: Whip evaporated milk until real fluffy.
Combine jello and hot water, mix all together and fold in whipped evaporated milk.
Pour into crust and sprinkle with dry cracker crumbs.
Place in refrigerator 8 hours.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix
oatmeal, butter and hot water and let stand.
Beat eggs, granulated	sugar,	brown
sugar
and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients
with
other ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Frost when hot.

title: sky-high strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, mash enough berries to equal 3 cups.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in mashed berries and water; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Chill for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture is slightly warm. Arrange remaining berries caps down in pie shell, layering.
Pour warm mixture over whole berries.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: bisquick biscuits
directions: Use muffin pan.
Makes
small
or 8 large biscuits. Cook at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: marinade for steak or chicken
directions: Mix together and pour over meat.
Marinate for at least 2 hours (overnight is better).
You can prick the meat with a fork to allow the marinade to seep through.
Also, you can turn the meat over several times during marinating.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and pour in one 9-inch or two 8-inch unbaked pie shells. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes longer.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour over pecans and coconut, then combine together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Melt on low heat. Pour over cake and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: two minute fudge
directions: In casserole, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together until partially blended (mixture is too stiff to thoroughly blend in all of the dry ingredients).
Put butter on top of mixture in center of dish.
Microwave 2 minutes or until milk feels warm on bottom of dish.
Stir vigorously until smooth. If all butter has not melted in cooking, it will as mixture is stirred.
Add nuts.
Blend well and pour into 8 x 4 x 3-inch dish (I spray it with Pam first).
Chill 1 hour in fridge or 20 to 30 minutes in freezer.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm in the middle.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in water with salt.
When done and still hot, stir in garlic cheese and 3/4 stick of butter.
Cool.
Add eggs in milk. Season with red pepper.
Pour in buttered baking dish.
Dot top with remainder of stick of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: eggs for a crowd
directions: Mix eggs with milk and scramble with margarine until soft and fluffy.
(I do 1/2 at a time.)
Mix soup with mushrooms.
In a large cake pan, layer 1/2 the eggs, 1/2 the sauce and 1/2 the grated cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Store overnight, covered.
Do not use tinfoil.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: melting moments
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients with mixer at medium speed.
Place dough in pastry bag and using star tip, form cookies onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes until lightly browned.
Can be decorated with colored sugar before baking, if desired.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and oil; add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: lemonade torte
directions: Line a 9 x 9-inch pan with graham cracker crust.
Put the next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; mix.
Put mixture in pan; sprinkle some crumbs over the top.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or longer, until set.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a heavy skillet over medium heat.
Transfer sausage to a 2 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
In the sausage drippings, saute celery, onion, sweet red pepper, green pepper and mushrooms until lightly browned.
Turn into casserole.
Add water chestnuts, rice, broth, salt and pepper to casserole; mix well. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until rice is fluffy and tender.

title: coconut dessert
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and press in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix milk, pudding and vanilla ice cream in a large bowl.
Spread on crust and top with 9 ounces Cool Whip.

title: tomato pickle
directions: Mix together and
cook over low heat until thick.
Pour into jars while still hot and seal.

title: round steak supreme
directions: Cut steak in 1-inch strips and brown in small amount of oil in skillet on top of stove.
Put all ingredients in covered casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in salt water until tender; drain well.
Melt butter.
Mix in salt and pepper; set aside.
Add all ingredients and 1/2 package of stuffing to squash.
Mix in butter mixture. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and allow to cool.
Add pineapple to jello and allow to set.
Prepare Dream Whip according to instructions on package and fold in jello and pineapple mixture.
Cut angel food cake in bite size pieces and put a layer in pan.
Add layers of jello mixture and cake and top with coconut.

title: cheesy o'brien potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes with mayonnaise and sour cream;
use as much as needed to mix well.
Pour into flat casserole.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix milk, eggs, salt, pepper and onion.
Place squash in buttered casserole.
Pour milk mixture over squash.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy velveeta dip
directions: Place Velveeta in a crock-pot to start melting.
Meanwhile, brown hamburger meat.
Drain and add to Velveeta. Add the Ro-Tel tomatoes and stir.
May double recipe. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: smothered steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge steak in flour mixture.
Brown in hot oil in a large heavy skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until steak is tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Mix in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add milk and yeast to flour.
When mixed, roll out 1/4 inch and cut.
Dip in melted butter and fold over.

title: beulah's meat loaf
directions: Add the crackers to mixture until thick enough.
(Use aluminum foil in bottom of pan).
Pour catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry confection
directions: This is a no bake cookie you shape and decorate to look like strawberries.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix in gallon jug and fill to the top with water. Chill before serving.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onions and garlic until meat is brown and onion tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook at low temperature for at least 2 hours or use crock-pot all afternoon.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: coconut carnival cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Drop in shortening.
Add milk and vanilla; beat 300 strokes (2 minutes at low speed, scraping bowl).
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes on low. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost and sprinkle with flaked coconut.

title: microwave salmon rice casserole
directions: Combine soup, salmon liquid and cheese in a microwave-safe casserole.
Stir well.
Cover and microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir at 1 minute.
Add salmon, broccoli and rice.
Cover and microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Stir at 2 minutes and at 6 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mama shapiro's famous baked spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 340°.
Boil spaghetti in salted water until soft.
Drain spaghetti.
Do not rinse.
Mix butter through at once so it won't stick.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together until hamburger is brown. Drain off fat.
Add cream of celery soup, salt and pepper to taste. Mix well.
Place in a casserole dish.
Cover with slices of cheese, then Tater Tots.
Put in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until Tater Tots are done.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil one chicken (4 breasts) and debone.
Add salt and pepper. Add 1/2 stick margarine to broth and 3 bouillon cubes.

title: santa cake
directions: Put milk and butter in the bowl.
Mix it up with the mixer. Put it in a pan to cook it.
Turn the oven on bake and cook it for 1 hour.
Then you take it out.
Put the frosting on it.

title: orange slush
directions: Mash bananas in blender.
Add all ingredients except 7-Up. Freeze 24 hours or longer, if needed.
Remove 1 hour before serving and add 7-Up.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Slowly beat in 2 well beaten eggs; cook until slightly thick, about 5 minutes.
Beat mayonnaise. Pour over potatoes, onions and hard-boiled eggs.

title: crouton hot dish
directions: Add butter to hot water and mix in the croutons until moist. Line 9 x 9-inch pan with 3/4 of the dressing.
Add layer of chicken.
Mix soups and milk; pour over chicken.
Top with rest of dressing and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter-crumbed chicken(weight watchers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In custard cup, melt butter in oven or microwave; stir in soy sauce.
Place bread crumbs on wax paper. Brush each drumstick with butter mixture; roll in crumb mixture until evenly coated.
Place drumsticks in single layer on baking pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until juices are clear when meat is pricked with a fork.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Remove skins from potatoes;
slice into
a
bowl. Saute onion in
cup melted butter until
tender.
Remove
from heat. Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over
potatoes and 1 cup cheese.
Toss well.
Pour into a greased 13
x
9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cheese.
Cover.
May be made ahead and refrigerated overnight. Bake
in
oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar, butter, milk and chocolate.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly.
When mixture comes to a boil, remove from heat.
Add vanilla; beat until thick enough to spread.

title: turkey chili(low-fat recipe)
directions: Brown turkey in a large pan sprayed with Pam until broken apart and brown.
Add green pepper and onion.
Reduce heat and cover.
Cook over medium heat until peppers are tender.
Add beans, tomatoes and chili mix.
Simmer 10 minutes and serve.

title: chipped beef bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, with electric mixer.
Hollow out bread to form a bowl and cube the excess bread.
Spoon mixture into bread bowl cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serve with cubed bread as dippers.

title: bacon cheese rolls
directions: Cut crusts from bread.
Roll flat with rolling pin.
Spread cheese soup on bread.
Roll tightly and cut in half.
Wrap with 1/2 strip of bacon.
Broil on cookie sheet, turning until bacon is done.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup strawberry juice for icing.
Mix first six ingredients until well blended.
Bake in three layer pans at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: vanilla pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs 1 minute on high.
Blend flour.
Add half of flour.
Beat 1 minute.
Add milk and remaining flour.
Add flavoring and beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Increase heat to 350° and bake for 10 minutes.
Bake in tube pan. Ice with your favorite icing.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend with mayonnaise and sugar.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in cream which has been whipped with confectioners sugar.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch container and freeze 6 hours.
Cut into squares.
Keep in freezer.
Seal well.
May be serve as a salad or dessert.

title: brenda's rice krispie cookies
directions: Melt Karo, peanut butter and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Pour over the Rice Krispies mixture.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and jello, mix well.
Add water, bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Let cool.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, cut and boil eggplants.
Fry onions, celery, bell pepper and
garlic
in
margarine.
Drain
and add eggplants; reserve water
and
other
seasonings.
Cook several minutes. Add chopped ham
and
mix
thoroughly.
If too dry, add small amounts of reserved
water.
Take from fire and add egg.
Put into casserole and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Scoop out zucchini
pulp; cook with raw rice, water and salt for 15
minutes,
covered.
Take
off
heat.
Add
grated cheese, egg (beaten), oregano, onion flakes and parsley.
Pile into shells.
Bake
at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle top with a little grated cheese when taken out of oven.

title: salmon and corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the 3 beaten eggs whites.
Fold in the 3 beaten egg whites and spoon into pan by tablespoon that is greased and fry until golden brown.

title: crock-pot catch-all soup(serves 10)
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients.
Place in crock-pot along with other ingredients.
Cook on high for 2 hours and on low for rest of day.
Add garlic powder and Lawry's seasoned salt to taste. Several hours before eating, top with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place chicken and broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, lemon juice, salt, pepper, curry powder and parsley flakes together; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken and rice
directions: Combine uncooked rice, soup and water in crock-pot, stir well. Put chicken in a roasting bag to coat chicken with onion soup mix.
Puncture 4 to 6 holes in bottom of bag and fold top of the bag over chicken and place in crock-pot on top of rice.
Cover and cook on low setting 8 to 10 hours.

title: quick broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in water or microwave until tender-crisp. Finely chop in a food processor or chopper.
Bring the chicken broth, onion flakes and rosemary to a boil.
Add the chopped broccoli.
Mix some of the milk with the flour until smooth. Gradually add flour and milk mixture to the broth mixture.
Slowly add the remaining milk and heat until flavors are blended.
(For a more colorful soup, use a package of broccoli, cauliflower and carrot mix.
For more chicken flavor, add a chicken bouillon cube.)

title: lace chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray baking sheet with Pam.

Set aside. In medium saucepan, melt oleo. Stir in brown sugar and corn syrup. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients until blended.
Drop mixture by teaspoon 3-inches apart on prepared baking sheet. Bake 9 minutes or until cookies spread thin and are deep brown.
(Cookies will be soft.)
Cool 2 minutes on sheet. Working quickly with spatula, remove cookies to wire rack. Cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired. Yields 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. For crust, beat butter at medium speed until smooth. Add powdered sugar; beat until well blended. Add flour gradually, beating at low speed after each addition. (Mixture will look crumbly but should press together easily.) Press dough evenly into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Press mixture slightly up sides of pan, less than 1/4-inch, to form lip to hold filling. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden
brown.

title: creole kisses
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat egg whites in small mixer bowl until foamy.
Beat in sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until very stiff and glossy.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake until dry, about 20 minutes (do not let candy brown). Immediately remove from baking sheet.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Fry in butter until brown. Add onion and celery.
Let simmer until onion is done.
Add raw rice, stir thoroughly.
Cover with chicken stock; add salt and pepper.
Let come to a boil.
Cover with lid or foil and let simmer in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Mix and let stand in fridge 1 hour.
Roll dough on lightly floured board and cut; sprinkle on sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: tuna salad on lettuce leaves
directions: Mix together tuna, mayonnaise, onion powder, and celery seed. Chill for 1/2 hour.
Spoon tuna salad onto lettuce leaves. Garnish with grated carrot and pickles.

title: aunt jan's apple crumble
directions: Place as many sliced apples as desired in baking dish.
Cover with the next 4 ingredients, which have been mixed together like a pie crust.
Bake at 350° until apples are soft.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt; mix in wheat germ.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until well blended.
Place in an oiled 8 x 4-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until done.
Yields 1 loaf, 16 slices.
Each slice contains 130 calories.

title: cocoa fudge cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and Crisco.
Add flour, soda, salt, cocoa, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into three cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Follow directions on cake mix but place in a large, deep cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until done. While cake is baking, make pudding as directions say and put in refrigerator until set.
When cake is cold, spread pudding on top. Beat cream cheese with can of pineapple (do not drain).
Put mixture on top of pudding.
Put Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
The longer it sits in the refrigerator, the better.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Mix all together and put in crock for 6 to 8 hours on low.

title: peachy pork chops(serves 6)
directions: Brown chops on both sides in large skillet.
Reduce to medium-low heat.
Meanwhile, blend a mixture of brown sugar, cinnamon and cloves with tomato sauce, reserved peach syrup and vinegar.
Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Place a peach half on each chop.
Pour sauce over all.
Cover skillet and simmer approximately 30 minutes or until pork is tender.
Baste occasionally with sauce.

title: quaker chocolate oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips; mix well.
Drop spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 13 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat soup and cheese until melted.
Add 1 can of milk.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add all together in casserole dish. Put in 350° oven uncovered for about 15 minutes.
Then cover for the rest of the time (10 minutes).

title: lush
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix flour and margarine like you do pie crust. Sprinkle a few slivered almonds over bottom.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lite ambrosia fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and yogurt until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 cups.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat 1 stick butter in 7 1/2 x 11 3/4 inch dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour mixture over hot butter in dish.
Rise and drain 3 pints blueberries. Spread berries evenly over surface. Top by sprinkling 1/4 to 1/2 cup sugar. Bake for about 50 minutes. Serve hot and add small scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: curried rice
directions: In medium skillet melt margarine.
Add onion, curry, garlic, cumin and poultry seasoning.
Cook until onion is tender, reduce heat to low.
With fork, stir in rice, raisins, parsley, orange juice and orange peel.
Heat through.

title: double good yeast rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients:
sugar, salt, lukewarm water, eggs and dry yeast.
Mix 2 minutes on low speed and set aside: flour, sugar, Crisco and water.
Combine this in large mixing bowl; mix flour and Crisco like you would for a pie crust.
Add sugar and water and mix 3 minutes with heavy-duty mixer at medium speed.
Add yeast mixture.
Mix 3 minutes.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Punch dough down.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
With floured hands, make round balls.
Put in muffin tins.
Let rise in warm place.
Bake at 350°.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cook asparagus until barely tender; drain.
In large pan, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in flour, then add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Mix in salt, pepper, eggs and asparagus.
Pour into a 2-qt. buttered casserole; top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees until hot and bubbly.

title: rich peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Melt butter and peanut butter in bowl over hot water.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
(I use 25 minutes.)
Cool and cut into squares.
Yield: about 24 squares.

title: special sausage and eggs
directions: Cook sausage over low heat until done and a crumbly consistency.
Drain and set aside.
Spread butter on bread and cut in cubes.
Place cubes in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle sausage on bread and cheese on top of sausage.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour over cheese.
Chill overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Let cool.
Add cranberries.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator to jell.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute the onion in the oleo.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pierogi (polish potato) casserole
directions: To mashed potatoes, add Cheddar cheese; beat with a mixer. Saut onions in butter until soft. Add 1/3 of onions to potato mixture, then salt to taste. Butter a 13 x 9 baking dish. Layer noodles, then potatoes and repeat, ending with noodles. Pour remaining butter and onions over top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° until heated through.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put in large bowl in order given.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix oil, dill, lemon pepper, garlic and Ranch dressing together.
Stir in oyster crackers.
Lay out on cookie sheet. Bake at 275° for 20 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad 2
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the dressing. Put light layer of dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Bake in pie shell for 50 to 60 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: glossy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over medium heat until thickened. Remove from heat.
Add 1 tablespoon of oleo and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins until tender.
Peel and slice thinly.
Broil bacon until crisp.
In skillet, heat 1/3 cup of bacon drippings.
Add flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper. Mix together vinegar and water.
Stir and gradually add vinegar and water to bacon fat mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Add onion and the crumbled bacon.
Stir through.
Serve warm.
This is Brad's mother's recipe.

title: emergency casserole
directions: Combine cabbage, then potatoes and onion.
Put into a 2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
On top, place the pork chops.
Add salt, pepper and water.
Cover.
Bake until done.

title: roast in foil
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with large piece of aluminum foil. Place roast on foil; sprinkle with
onion
soup.
Mix mushroom soup with water.
Pour over roast.
Place
another
piece
of foil over top and seal edges well.
Bake
in preheated 325° to 350°
for
1 hour per pound or until
done.
Remove
roast
to platter and gravy into gravy dish.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: In a saucepan, mix together sugar and cocoa. gradually stir in milk. Heat over a medium flame and add margarine. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil. Let boil for a minute or two. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and quick oats. Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet. Can be cooled in fridge.

title: raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins, margarine and water for 5 minutes.
In a separate bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Add the raisin mixture to the dry ingredients and blend well. Pour into an unbaked shell and bake at 350°.

title: potato dish
directions: Leave skin on potatoes; boil potatoes and drain. Mash with butter and milk. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add sour cream, onions and chives. Spoon into buttered Pyrex dish (12 x 12). Cover with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: six layer dip
directions: Spread the refried beans in the bottom of a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese; cover. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes. Remove cover. Continue baking until cheese melts. Remove from oven. Spread sour cream over beans. Top with lettuce, tomato and onions. Serve immediately with tortilla chips. Makes about 3 1/2 cups dip.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Take aluminum foil and butter the non-shiny side.
Dice 2 large potatoes onto foil.
Place 2 ice cubes in potatoes.
Cut up onions and peppers; salt and pepper to taste.
Fold foil up on top and sides; seal completely.
Repeat steps for the last 2 potatoes. Place on grill 15 to 20 minutes before meat.
Cook the whole time meat is on the grill.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: oatmeal cocoa chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt and set aside.
In large mixing bowl combine margarine, sugars and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in morsels, oats and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes for chewy cookies, 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies. Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Pour 1 gallon of boiling water over cucumbers.
Add salt.
Let pickles stand for 1 week; stir every day.
Drain and add 1 gallon boiling water and alum.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and make a syrup of sugar, vinegar and pickling spices (put spices in a white cloth and tie it).
Heat syrup and pour over cucumbers for three mornings.
On the fourth morning, heat syrup and can cucumbers. Seal at once.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion; drain and mash with a fork.
Melt butter and add 1/2 package of stuffing.
Add remaining ingredients to squash.

title: hot dog enchiladas
directions: Split each wiener and fill with onions and grated cheese.
Dip each tortilla in hot grease just enough to soften.
Roll tortillas around wieners.
Place in a casserole dish.
Pour hot chili over all tortillas and sprinkle with remaining cheese and onion.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain off fat.
Add chopped onion.
Saute. Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Put on simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: old fashioned sour cream cutout cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternating with sour cream.
Divide dough and roll out to 1/4-inch thickness on well floured pastry board. Cut out desired shapes.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, add flour; season and stir until smooth.
Slowly add hot milk, stirring constantly.
When mixture thickens, melt grated cheese and American cheese in sauce.
Put layers of sliced potatoes, onions and cheese sauce into buttered baking dish.
Repeat all ingredients until gone.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: meal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie shell. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: The zucchini should be shredded coarsely and handled as little as possible to avoid making it watery.

title: buttermilk rolls(makes 24 medium-sized rolls)
directions: Warm buttermilk.
Combine warm water and yeast; stir until softened.
Sift flour once.
Measure.
Add sugar, salt and soda and sift into mixing bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture; beat until smooth and blended.
Dough will be soft, like a stiff batter.
Cover with foil or plastic wrap; refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: cauliflower with mushroom sauce
directions: Arrange cauliflower in baking dish and set aside.
Melt margarine in small pan.
Add mushrooms and scallions and saute for 1 minute.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until flour is absorbed.
Stirring continuously, pour in milk until slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until top is lightly brown.
Serves 4.

title: crazy coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender, beat on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Let stand 5 minutes. Sprinkle with coconut on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or Bundt pan.
Sift first 5 ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Melt Crisco in 2 cups hot water.
Beat eggs in medium size bowl.
Continue to beat slowly while pouring liquid slowly into eggs.
Pour liquid through sieve into dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Bake for approximately 45 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with fluffy white icing.
Garnish with crushed peppermint stick (optional).

title: blue ribbon banana cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add mashed bananas.
Beat 2 minutes.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture along with buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts. Turn into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut on each layer.
Bake in a moderate (375°) oven 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool layers, coconut side up, on rack. Place first layer coconut side down and spread on filling.
Top with second layer, coconut side up.
Swirl White Snow Frosting around sides and about 1 inch around top edge, leaving center unfrosted.

title: mocha pound cake
directions: Stir Shortening to soften. Sift in flour, sugar, instant coffee, salt, cream of tartar, and soda. Add water and vanilla. Mix until flour is dampened then beat vigorously 2 minutes using electric mixer. Add eggs and unsweetened chocolate. Beat 1 minute longer. Pour into paper lined loaf pan.

title: tomato relish
directions: Boil on low heat until thick; put in jars and seal.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You will need a punch bowl.

title: crab meat soup
directions: Thicken with cornstarch.
Bring to a boil.
Drop in beaten eggs.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Prepare and add the following layers:

title: millionaire cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick butter.
Line pan with mixture.
Mix beaten eggs, sugar and 1 stick of butter.
Spread on top of crumbs.
Layer bananas, pineapple and Cool Whip on top. Top with cherries and nuts.

title: mary ellen's chicken
directions: Marinate first 6 ingredients in dressing for 2 plus hours. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: For French toast, use cookie cutters to make toy shapes.
Add mini chocolate chips to pancake batter.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain vegetables and pour into a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and let stand overnight.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chocolate chips); press into a cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over the top.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring to boil the Karo, sugar and peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add Special K; mix quickly.
Put into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Melt chocolate bits and spread over top.

title: corned beef salad
directions: After jello is jelled (makes 2 cups), beat with mixer until light and bubbly.
Mix in mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate to set.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix margarine and oil; add powdered sugar and sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, cream of tartar, soda, and salt.
Add creamed mixture.
Roll in small balls.
Mash with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place 1/2 can shrimp and remaining ingredients in blender or electric mixer; blend until fluffy and smooth.
Coarsely chop remaining shrimp; fold into mixture.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve with favorite crackers.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Heat butter, cocoa and Coke until boiling.
Pour combined mixture over flour and sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda, vanilla and marshmallows. Beat together; mix well.
Will make a thin batter with marshmallows on top.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: salsa cruda
directions: Blanch the tomatoes, then peel, seed and coarsely chop them. Combine all ingredients except salt.
Let sit about 30 minutes to allow flavors to mix.
Add salt to taste and serve.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef until all pink is gone.
Pork drippings.
Add onions and garlic; mix thoroughly.
Stir in enchilada sauce mix and taco seasoning mix.
Add tomato paste, soup and jalapenos.
Add water slowly; cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Beginning with a thin layer of meat sauce, alternate layers of sauce, tortillas and grated cheese in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish until all ingredients are used, ending with cheese.
Bake at 325°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: special k treats
directions: Melt peanut butter, sugar, oleo and Karo syrup; mix in Special K.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan greased with butter.

title: bread pudding with bourbon sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream together the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, cream, cinnamon, vanilla and raisins, mixing well.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan 1 3/4-inch deep. Arrange bread slices flat in egg mixture and let stand for 5 minutes to soak.
Turn bread over and let stand 10 minutes longer. Then push bread down so that most of it is covered.
Set pan in a larger pan filled with water 1/2-inch from the top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Uncover pudding for the last 10 minutes to brown the top.
When done, the custard should be soft, not firm.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill can of evaporated milk 3 to 4 hours.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and chill until partially set.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Whip chilled milk and fold into Jell-O mixture.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with half of crumbs.
Pour mixture over crumbs and top with remaining crumbs. Chill several hours or overnight.
Cut in squares and center each square with a maraschino cherry.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter, and cocoa, add egg, water and vanilla, mix well. Mix dry ingredients and add to cream mixture. Grease cookie sheet, drop by spoonfuls and bake at 350 degrees for about 10 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in 6 to 8 cups water overnight or bring to boil, boil for 2 minutes, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Rinse thoroughly.
Put beans in fresh water (6 to 8 cups) and bring to boil.
Add chopped pepper, onion, garlic and summer sausage.
Reduce heat to simmer for 2 hours (add water if necessary).
Add vinegar and Tabasco to taste.
Serve over rice. You can also do this in crock-pot.
Soak beans overnight, rinse. Add ingredients and cook on slow all day.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple together until Jell-O granules dissolve. Add cottage cheese and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill.

title: dessert latija
directions: Slice cake and lay on bottom of a platter.
Place 1 1/3 cups water in a saucepan.
Bring it almost to a boil and add milk and sugar.
Mix remaining 1/3 cup water with cornstarch and vanilla. Gradually add to the milk mixture, stirring constantly until mixture is thick and there are no lumps.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Stir in eggs, one-fourth at a time, while stirring vigorously.
After all egg has been mixed in, return to heat and cook on low heat for 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened.
Pour Latija on top of sponge cake and sprinkle with plenty of cinnamon. Serves 12.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir sugar and milk until well blended.
Add butter and salt; cook over medium heat until soft ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter, stirring until it melts.
Immediately beat with electric mixer about 5 minutes or until thick enough to spread.
Pour into well-buttered pan, cut and serve.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli buds, discarding thick stems.
Peel and chop onion.
Mix broccoli, chopped onion, shredded cheese and bacon in large mixing bowl.
Mix the least 3 ingredients in small bowl; add to broccoli mixture.
Marinate in refrigerator for at least 8 hours before serving.

title: fruit leather
directions: Puree fruit in a blender.
Heat fruit puree or applesauce in a saucepan until heated through.
Add spices if desired.
Blend again.
Cover a cookie sheet with plastic wrap.
Pour the fruit puree onto cookie sheet and spread with a spatula.
Bake at 150° for 8 hours.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in vanilla, butter flavoring, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon into three (9-inch) round greased and floured cake pans.
Check with toothpick until it comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: caramel corn(like cracker jacks)
directions: Pop the corn; remove unpopped kernels and set aside.
Cook remaining ingredients over low heat to 240° or soft ball stage (2 minute boil).
Remove from heat, then add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Put in 2 large dripper pans (I use 2 cookie sheets); put in 200° oven for 45 minutes. Remove onto waxed paper and cool.

title: garden stir-fry #2
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken; stir until no longer pink.
Add vegetables; stir-fry until vegetables are just tender-crisp.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Add to spaghetti; toss to mix.
Add a salad and dessert to make a complete meal. Serves 4.

title: green beans and bacon
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and drain.
Cook and stir onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: red beans with ham and rice
directions: Put water and bouillon cube in a 4-quart Dutch oven; bring to a boil over high heat.
Stir in rice.
When liquid boils again, stir in all remaining ingredients, except the tomatoes.
Return mixture to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes or until rice is tender and most of liquid is absorbed. Turn off heat.
Add tomatoes and stir gently.
Let stand covered for 5 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Bring to boil the pineapple juice, sugar, vinegar, egg and flour.
Cool.
Mix together Cool Whip, crushed peanuts and apples with above.
I use the extra creamy Cool Whip.
You can also sprinkle peanuts on top.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix.
May chill overnight.
Form into small balls.
Flatten with glass that has been dipped in sugar each time.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 100 to 120 cookies.

title: peach cheesecake trifle
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend cream cheese and powdered sugar. Add the sour cream, vanilla and almond extract.
In a small bowl, whip the heavy cream until stiff.
Add the vanilla and sugar.
Fold the whipped cream into the cream cheese mixture.
Add the cake cubes and coat well.
Thickly slice peaches; add the sugar and mix well.
Layer into a trifle bowl, starting with a layer of peaches, then cake cream mixture.
Continue layering, ending with peaches. Cover with plastic wrap and chill.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook meat and onion.
Drain off excess grease. Add cumin, garlic, chili powder, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer for about 10 minutes until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Pour 1/2 taco sauce in bottom of baking dish. Cut 6 tortillas in strips and put in bottom of dish.
Pour 1/2 cup sauce evenly over tortillas. Spoon in meat mixture and top with sour cream.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the cheese. Arrange last 6 tortillas over cheese. Spread rest of the sauce over the tortillas.
Top with rest of cheese.
Cover with foil and bake for 40 minutes at 375°.
Remove foil and continue baking for 5 more minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: orange cake
directions: In food processor, grind raisins and orange rind.
Mix with buttermilk.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda, shortening and salt.
Combine dry ingredients with fruit and milk mixture and beat 1 1/2 minutes with electric mixer.
Add eggs and beat another 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into large greased pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix sugar, butter, peanut butter and Rice Krispies and form into 1-inch balls.
Melt chips and paraffin.
Dip balls into chocolate.
Let stand until firm.

title: fudge
directions: Mix in a bowl the nuts, chocolate chips and butter.
Set aside.
In a pan mix evaporated milk, sugar and marshmallows. Bring to a boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into chocolate mix until chocolate melts or dissolves.
Put into shallow buttered and greased pan.
Let set in refrigerator until cool.

title: fresh cucumber relish
directions: Slice cucumbers in half, lengthwise.
Scoop out seed and discard.
Grind cucumbers and onion in food grinder and drain. Stir in vinegar, sugar, salt and dill weed.
Chill for 8 hours or overnight.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Cook meat until done and drain.
Mix noodles, meat, soup, corn and sour cream together.
Put in baking dish and bake at 450° until heated through.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into mold or 9-inch square cake pan to be cut into squares.
Freeze.

title: toffee bars
directions: Chop pecans very fine.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish and spread the pecans evenly.
Melt margarine sticks; add brown sugar. Dissolve and stir constantly while boiling.
Boil for 7 minutes. Quickly spread over nuts.
Break up Hershey's bars in small pieces; place on top of sugar mixture and spread evenly.
Cut or break in small pieces.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make in a trifle bowl.
Looks great!
Prepare white cake mix and bake.
Prepare cake in a round cake pan.
Slice cake in half. Place one half in bowl.
Place 1/2 can crushed pineapple over cake.
Sprinkle instant vanilla pudding (dry) over pineapple. Slice 1 1/2 bananas, place on top of pudding.
Place 1/2 pint of strawberries over bananas.
Place 1/2 container of Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts.
Repeat this process.

title: herb-cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cut bread diagonally into 1-inch slices. Mix remaining ingredients; spread on slices.
Reassemble half loaf and wrap securely in heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Bake 25 minutes. Makes about 12 slices.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in a deep pan.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for at least 1 hour.

title: holiday salad
directions: Stir together Cool Whip and milk.
Then add other ingredients and stir together.

title: papeete punch
directions: Multiply quantities of ingredients to make the total amount needed.
Have all juices chilled thoroughly.
Mix ingredients together in punch bowl.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: Cut potatoes into halves.
Cook with onion in 2 cups boiling water until tender; let stand.
Mash potatoes.
Add sausage, spices, sharp cheeses and remaining boiling water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan just before serving.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Wash and thoroughly dry prawns.
Season the prawns with salt and pepper.
To the melted butter in a baking pan, add the garlic, parsley and prawns.
Bake in a 350° oven until heated through, approximately 20 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into balls.
Then roll balls in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together and pour into a chocolate graham cracker crust. Use a plain Hershey bar to top with chocolate shavings. Refrigerate and serve.
This makes 2 pies.

title: cherry tomato salad
directions: Wash and stem tomatoes.
Dry completely.
Cook bacon until very crisp; drain thoroughly on paper towels.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, olive oil, salt and basil.
Pour over tomatoes, crumble bacon over all and stir to coat tomatoes with dressing.
Serve at once or refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yield:
6 servings. Carbohydrate 15 g, protein 10 g, fat 16 g, calories 237.

title: beef and macaroni skillet meal
directions: On high, brown onion and meat mixture together.
Add macaroni, tomatoes and seasoning.
Place cover over skillet.
When steam comes from vent, turn to low.
Allow to cook 30 minutes.
Do not remove the lid during the cooking period.

title: whip cream frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk slowly together; cook until thick.
Cool. Mix Crisco, sugar and vanilla.
Add thickened and cooled milk. Beat 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Add water to make 2 cups.
Boil juice and add jello.
Put in refrigerator until partly jelled.
Beat cheese and salad dressing until fluffy.
Fold in Dream Whip and jello.
Add fruit; keep cold until set and serve.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Drain and hold. Combine chives, parsley, Parmesan cheese, Ricotta cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Gently spoon into shells.
Spread marinara sauce on bottom of pan.
Gently place in shells; open side down.
Cover with marinara sauce.
